./observations/claude/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held.md:11:The teaching 'use a method, then release it and do not own the result' is not a general law about how practices end. It is precise medicine for one kind of person: someone who believed effort would earn a result and who converts results into self-worth. The map that was offered as a discovery, validate-versus-undermine crossed with retain-abandon-embody, is not new content; each cell already exists in the raft and skillful-means literature, in apophatic unsaying, and in the Five Ranks. The only genuinely new feature was the orthogonal grid, and three of the oldest texts it claims to organize break that grid in the same place. Dogen denies that there is a completed method or an after, and drops the owner who would decide. Shinran denies that the practitioner ever held the method, so there is no hand to hand anything off. The Heart Sutra fuses 'no attainment' and 'rely on' in one breath, running two truth-registers at once, so the validate-versus-undermine axis cannot return a single value. Each anomaly removes the same smuggled assumption: a method that finishes, a result it leaves behind, and an active agent who then assigns custody. Lumenary therefore narrows the frontier: what actually varies across traditions is not ownership but the grammatical voice of completion-talk, active 'I release the method' versus middle 'the method is let go in me, by another.' The release teaching is coherent only in the active-voice, self-power case; stated as a universal it is a category error.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held.md:22:- Prior-art audit: Michael A. Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying (Chicago, 1994): the self-undermining 'meaning event' is already a cross-tradition discovery across Plotinus, Eriugena, Ibn Arabi, Porete, Eckhart; custody appears only obliquely as dispossession.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held.md:24:- Prior-art audit: the Eckhart Gelassenheit / Heidegger releasement / Dzogchen rang grol cluster already attests all three custody poles (retain, abandon, embody-without-ownership).
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held.md:151:- Prediction: If the two-axis custody model is a discovery, at least one cell (one combination of validate-or-undermine with retain, abandon, or embody) should lack a clear prior instantiation. The audit found every cell already attested: Smith and the raft for validated-then-released, Sells and mushotoku for self-undermining, the Five Ranks and Gelassenheit and rang grol for embodied-without-ownership. If a future search finds an unattested cell that does predictive work, the retirement is weakened.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held.md:161:- Prediction: If the model is general, hard cases should land as determinate values of the custody axis. Instead Dogen, Shinran, and the Heart Sutra should each void the method-then-result-then-custody timeline the grid needs, breaking it at the same joint. If a careful reading shows any of the three actually occupies a clean grid cell without collapsing the timeline, the narrowing is weakened.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held.md:176:### Voice versus custody as the better classifier
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held.md:181:- Prediction: If voice is the real variable, blind coders sorting completion-talk by grammatical voice (active, middle, passive) should predict a tradition's supervision, warning, and re-entry patterns better than coders sorting the same texts by retain-abandon-embody custody value. If custody value predicts these better, the relocation to voice fails and the original axis should be kept.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held.md:184:- Next action: Build two code sheets, one for voice and one for custody, and test both against held-out warning and re-entry passages from eight traditions.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held.md:189:- If this narrowing is right, then coding completion-talk for grammatical voice (active, middle, passive) should sort traditions better than coding them for the retain-abandon-embody custody value. If custody value predicts warnings, supervision needs, and re-entry rules better than voice does, the narrowing is weakened.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:12:Transformative paths begin by placing unstable attention, trust, agency, and interpretation under custody before the practitioner can fully authorize or understand the path. Traditions then give that custody an entry grammar. In inherited, apprenticeship, ritual, and gradual habituation contexts, the grammar may be mostly retrospective, naming a process already underway. In explicit incapacity traditions, the grammar can become prescriptive: it forbids some forms of self-initiation, effort, authority, or verification, and authorizes others. The beginning of a path is therefore a contested custody arrangement whose doctrine may be either narration or control surface.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:21:- The beginning of a path is not reducible to first break, social induction, doctrine, or institution alone, but to an interaction between custody assignment, entry grammar, and practical control surface.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:31:Structural observation: Orange is the strongest prescriptive incapacity case: faith's beginning, desire, assent, prayer, and right choice are assigned to grace rather than unaided natural power. Tannisho and Ofumi give a vow-held analogue: entrusting is given by Amida's working, nenbutsu after settled faith is gratitude rather than self-powered production, and the warning profile targets calculation and self-power. Benedict gives institutional and apprenticeship custody: the novice is delayed, tested, placed under a senior, repeatedly exposed to the Rule, and only then incorporated. SN 55.5 is a partial anomaly: it names association with people of integrity, hearing true Dhamma, appropriate attention, and practice in accordance with Dhamma. That is distributed support, but not necessarily a doctrine forbidding self-generated beginning. The close-read result is that the candidate's structure exists in several sources, but its categories are analyst abstractions over older grace, vow, rule, apprenticeship, and stream-entry grammars.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:35:Risk of overread: Very high. Custody is a modern analyst term that can flatten grace, vow, obedience, refuge, rule, catechesis, initiation, community socialization, and practice-realization into one psychological metaphor. The model also risks circularity if the same passage is used to infer custody grammar and then to confirm predicted warnings or repairs.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:39:- "prescriptive custody" religious beginnings grace vow apprenticeship
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:52:- Local prior Lumenary record, observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger.md: overlap: Near exact. It already says a path begins when entry-state capacity is held somewhere in the person-world field, including practitioner, teacher, community, text, ritual, crisis, vow, institution, or latent awareness. It also says grammar is not merely retrospective and tells practitioners what not to claim, what to trust, what to repeat, what to fear, and what must be verified.; difference: The current candidate renames the support relation as custody and foregrounds the retrospective versus prescriptive distinction more sharply.; novelty impact: Very high reduction. Against internal prior art, this is mostly renamed and consolidated rather than new.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:53:- Local prior Lumenary audit, reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md: overlap: Very close. That audit already codes entry grammar, predicts safeguards and beginner warnings, requires split-source testing, and compares grace, vow, stream-entry, and practice-realization under translation strain.; difference: The current candidate drops translation-strain scoring and adds the language of custody as the beginning's support holder.; novelty impact: Very high reduction. The operational testing burden is inherited almost unchanged.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:54:- Lewis R. Rambo, Understanding Religious Conversion, Yale University Press, https://yalebooks.yale.edu/book/9780300065152/understanding-religious-conversion/: overlap: Very close for conversion as a multidimensional process shaped by context, crisis, quest, encounter, interaction, commitment, consequences, roles, rituals, rhetoric, and identity change.; difference: Rambo does not isolate custody of unstable attention, trust, agency, and interpretation, nor distinguish retrospective from prescriptive entry doctrine as a control surface.; novelty impact: High reduction for the process account. The remaining contribution would need to show predictive lift beyond Rambo-style conversion variables.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:55:- Jean Lave and Etienne Wenger, Situated Learning, chapter on legitimate peripheral participation, https://www.cambridge.org/highereducation/books/situated-learning/6915ABD21C8E4619F750A4D4ACA616CD/legitimate-peripheral-participation-in-communities-of-practice/B27B920BABACE5EF83276572EA0EF2C7: overlap: Very close for beginners participating before mastery, full understanding, or stable identity while community practice, artifacts, roles, discourse, and old-timers hold the learning process.; difference: Lave and Wenger do not treat spiritual beginning as doctrinally assigned custody, nor do they distinguish prescriptive incapacity doctrines from retrospective formation narratives.; novelty impact: High reduction for apprenticeship, inherited, and gradual habituation cases.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:56:- Helena Kupari and Terhi Utriainen, Newcomers Learning Religious Ritual: Legitimate Peripheral Participation in an Orthodox Worshipping Community, https://doi.org/10.30664/ar.136236: overlap: Close empirical near-neighbor. It studies religious newcomers learning embodied Orthodox ritual through real services, old-timer dynamics, and legitimate peripheral participation.; difference: It studies micro-sociological ritual learning, not custody assignment across grace, vow, rule, teacher, ritual, and practice-realization grammars.; novelty impact: High reduction for the social-induction side. It pressures the candidate to prove that doctrine adds prediction beyond embodied participation and community learning.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:57:- George Lindbeck, doctrine-as-grammar and cultural-linguistic religion, summarized at https://www.saet.ac.uk/Christianity/TheologicalLanguage and https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm: overlap: Close for doctrine as grammar that shapes speech, practice, identity, and what counts as coherent religious participation.; difference: Lindbeck's grammar model is broader and not specifically about beginnings, custody holders, or predictive testing of warnings and repairs.; novelty impact: High reduction for the entry-grammar concept.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:58:- Kenneth Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for distributing agency between person and God through self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles, with different practical outcomes.; difference: Pargament studies coping and problem solving, not initiation or the first authorization of transformative practice under grace, vow, teacher, rule, ritual, or community custody.; novelty impact: High reduction for agency-distribution and self-agency claims.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:60:- Shinran and Rennyo, Tannisho and Ofumi, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf: overlap: Near exact for vow-held beginning, Other Power, blocked self-credit, critique of calculation, and gratitude rather than self-powered production after entrusting.; difference: Pure Land texts are primary cases, not a general theory of prescriptive versus retrospective custody.; novelty impact: Very high reduction for vow-held and anti-self-power examples.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:61:- Rule of St. Benedict, chapter 58, https://archive.osb.org/rb/text/rbeaad2.html: overlap: Close for institutional custody of beginning: delayed entrance, testing, novice master supervision, rule-reading, free departure before vows, and later binding incorporation.; difference: Benedict is a formation rule with explicit institutional testing, not a theory of unstable attention and interpretation across traditions.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction for rule-held and apprenticeship-held beginning.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:66:Unlike prior Lumenary entry ledgers, Rambo conversion theory, legitimate peripheral participation, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament's agency styles, Orange, Shinran, Benedict, and OCIA, this candidate's only distinct claim is that beginnings should be coded as custody of unstable attention, trust, agency, and interpretation, and that entry doctrine should be classified as either retrospective narration or prescriptive control. That difference is useful but thin, because prior Lumenary records and older sources already contain most of the structure.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:72:Why it strains the model: The candidate assumes a distinguishable beginning where some holder takes custody before the practitioner can authorize the path. Dogen-style practice-realization weakens the before-after sequence because practice and realization are not two separate states. Inherited religion can make beginning indistinguishable from ordinary socialization. Successful dual practice can show multiple support systems coexisting without a single contested custody arrangement.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:74:Confidence effect: This lowers confidence in the model as a general theory. It can survive only as a coding heuristic with mandatory values for no-threshold, inherited-practice, practice-realization, simultaneous-custody, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:78:- If: Prescriptive custody grammar has incremental predictive force after social, institutional, and conversion-process controls. Then: Coders using only entry or doctrinal texts should predict held-out beginner warnings, verification rules, and repair instructions better when custody holder and prescriptive versus retrospective function are added to Rambo-style and Lave-Wenger-style variables. Weakens if: The added fields do not improve prediction, or all signal is absorbed by institution, teacher authority, socialization, ritual process, clinical risk, or tradition identity. Test surface: Split-source blind coding across Orange, Tannisho or Ofumi, Benedictine novitiate texts, OCIA, SN 55.5 and related Theravada manuals, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra entry source, and one Sufi or Islamic initiation source.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:79:- If: Explicit incapacity traditions should show warnings against the forbidden claimant named by the entry grammar. Then: Grace-held and vow-held cases should warn against self-credit, calculation, unaided assent, self-powered effort, premature assurance, or unauthorized verification more specifically than apprenticeship or socialization cases. Weakens if: Warnings are generic beginner warnings, such as laziness, poor ethics, weak motivation, or weak community belonging, and do not track the custody holder after controls. Test surface: Held-out warnings from Christian grace manuals, Shin Buddhist pastoral texts, Pure Land sermons, and teacher interviews.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:80:- If: Retrospective custody grammar should appear where lived induction precedes explicit doctrinal understanding. Then: Practitioners in inherited, ritual, monastic, or apprenticeship contexts should report that routine, community, sponsor, rule, liturgy, or family practice held attention and trust before doctrinal explanation became clear. Weakens if: Reports show doctrine-first authorization, or repair practices target belief assent more than formation ecology. Test surface: Interviews with cradle practitioners, OCIA participants, Orthodox catechumens, Buddhist refuge students, and monastic novices.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:81:- If: Hybrid instability should increase when old and new custody grammars assign agency and verification incompatibly. Then: Switching failures should cluster around self-verification, surrender, teacher trust, vow misunderstanding, grace versus effort, rule obedience, or ritual belonging rather than only technique mismatch. Weakens if: Breakdowns are predicted as well or better by intensity, trauma history, community conflict, practice technique, teacher misconduct, or clinical vulnerability. Test surface: Practitioner switching interviews coded against VCE-style practitioner, practice, relationship, interpretation, and health-factor baselines.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:98:- Is custody of beginning more than your ordinary language for grace, vow, refuge, obedience, rule, teacher transmission, socialization, apprenticeship, catechesis, or ritual incorporation?
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:101:- Which cases in your tradition reject the analyst's categories of custody, authorization, threshold, or beginning?
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:104:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners and scholars say the frame is ordinary grace theology, Other Power, catechumenate, monastic formation, refuge, initiation, lineage pedagogy, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, conversion studies, or legitimate peripheral participation. They cannot identify repairs predicted by custody grammar beyond institution, teacher experience, community ecology, temperament, or clinical risk.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:106:Answers that support contribution: Practitioners provide concrete failed-beginning cases where repair turned on misplaced authority, unsupported trust, self-verification, effort ownership, vow misunderstanding, teacher dependence, or ritual belonging, and where prescriptive versus retrospective custody predicts warnings or repairs better than standard conversion, formation, coping, or social-learning categories.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:116:Would count against it: Warning and repair profiles are predicted better by symptom severity, legal liability, institutional culture, supervision quality, mentor style, or workload than by entry grammar and custody assignment.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:124:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.76 to about 0.43. The candidate is generative, but most of its structure is already present in local Lumenary records, especially Entry-State Ledger, Threshold Grammar Under Translation Strain, Compound Entry Grammar, Layered Authorization of Beginning, and Operational Remainder Ecology. External near-neighbors further reduce the claim: Rambo covers conversion process, Lave and Wenger cover pre-mastery participation, Kupari and Utriainen apply that to religious newcomers, Lindbeck covers doctrine as grammar, Pargament covers agency distribution, Orange and Shinran give near-exact prescriptive beginning cases, Benedict and OCIA give institutional formation cases. The remaining contribution is a sharper label for prescriptive versus retrospective custody, not a discovery-level idea.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:130:- Build one bounded split-source coding sheet with fields for entry context, custody holder, entry grammar, retrospective versus prescriptive function, forbidden claimant, authorized support holder, verification rule, warning profile, repair practice, evidence passage, source layer, analyst-frame refusal, and confidence.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:132:- Add mandatory values for inherited practice, no-threshold, practice-realization, gradual socialization, ritual-held custody, community-held custody, teacher-held custody, vow-held custody, grace-held custody, rule-held custody, text-held custody, self-authorized entry, simultaneous custody, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:137:- Do not raise above renamed or extended unless blind coding shows that custody grammar predicts held-out warning, verification, and repair patterns better than entry-only, socialization-only, agency-style, institution, tradition-identity, teacher-style, and clinical-risk baselines.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-residual-burden-of-proof-after-negation-735d12569e257535.json:80:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.79 to about 0.48. This is a refinement of residue policy and overlaps strongly with Advaita self-luminosity, Buddhist not-self strategy, and Madhyamaka refusal of extremes.",
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-can-boundary-operation-and-custody-rule-be-coded-independently-of-the-verificatio.md:1:# Dialogue Convergence: Can boundary operation and custody rule be coded independently of the verificatio...
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-can-boundary-operation-and-custody-rule-be-coded-independently-of-the-verificatio.md:13:Can boundary operation and custody rule be coded independently of the verification and reentry patterns they are meant to explain, at comparable stages and genres, and still predict new cases better than stage, genre, institution, or doctrinal content?
./observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-verification-architecture-how-a-tradition-proves-insight-constitutes-what-insight-can-be.md:72:- Examine whether the verification architecture predicts the shadow location more precisely than the existing shadow model. If self-certifying architectures reliably produce unfalsifiable certainty, teacher-certifying architectures produce institutional corruption, and template-matching architectures produce scripted conformity, the verification architecture adds predictive power to the shadow model beyond what the epistemic organ or custody policy provides alone.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release.md:11:The two-axis rebuild of this frontier (a method validates or undermines its result, and the result is retained, abandoned, or embodied) silently assumes two things: that the practitioner owns the method, and that there is an 'after' in which custody of the result gets decided. A named class of practice breaks both assumptions. In radical Other Power (Shinran's jinen honi), the practitioner never owns the method, the trust, or the result; entrusting is given, not produced, and calculation is forbidden. In practice-realization (Dogen's shusho-itto), there is no after; verification is not expected outside the act, so no completion event exists at which custody is assigned. For these, the question 'what does a method do with its own authority' is not answered on either axis. It is refused or never arises. So the model is bounded, not universal: it applies only where a tradition grants the practitioner provisional ownership of a method and posits a discrete completion. The modern corollary sharpens the limit. For people whose wound is depleted agency, burnout to collapse or depression, prompting them to 'decide what to keep, release, and embody' can hand an exhausted self one more stewardship task, reproducing the very over-management the practice was meant to relieve.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release.md:15:Earlier findings repeatedly list Dogen and Shinran as anomalies to absorb into a wider custody model. This treats them instead as a boundary the model cannot cross, and converts non-ownership and non-temporality into explicit scope conditions. The second distinct move is to tie that boundary to a cohort for whom the custody prompt itself is contraindicated: the question 'what will you keep, release, or embody' presupposes a self with surplus agency to spend on stewardship, which is exactly what the burned-out person lacks. Prior work asks how a mature practitioner relates to a result; this asks who the question is even askable of, and warns that the prompt can wound the people most drawn to it.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release.md:22:- Primary text comparison: Dogen, Bendowa, shusho-itto. 'Do not expect verification outside of practice, for the practice is itself original verification.' This denies the temporal gap (method, then result, then a custody decision) that the two-axis model presupposes. https://www.sotozen.com/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf and https://zenstudiespodcast.com/bendowa-2/
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release.md:23:- The comparison reveals that Other Power answers 'who owns the method' with 'no one', and practice-realization answers 'when is the custody decision made' with 'there is no after'. The two-axis question is not resolved on either axis; it fails to arise.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release.md:30:A defender can fold the anomalies back in: 'undermining' or 'dissolving' already covers Other Power and practice-realization, since both still describe how a practitioner relates to a result. The narrowing may also be overdrawn. Shin still has nembutsu and warnings, and Soto still has zazen and cautions, so there is something the practitioner relates to and is corrected about; the custody question may be reframed rather than abolished. The cohort claim risks paternalism: some depleted people are helped precisely by being told to set things down, so 'do not give them the custody prompt' could withhold a useful instruction. And the MN 1 lens biases me to read every ownership word as grasping, which can make confident traditions like Advaita, where the witness is genuinely recognized and held, look like errors when they are not. If split-source coding shows Tannisho and Bendowa do use retain, release, or embody language about the practitioner's relation to method, the boundary collapses and the two-axis model survives as universal.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release.md:156:- Next action: Search comparative mysticism, Pure Land other-power scholarship, Dogen practice-realization scholarship, and apophatic theology for any existing statement that custody or completion models fail where the method is unowned or where there is no after.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release.md:166:- Next action: Code Tannisho chapters 1, 6, and 11, Shinran's letters on jinen honi, and Bendowa for whether custody language about the practitioner's relation to method appears or is refused, using a passage layer separate from any predicted warning.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release.md:191:- If this model is bounded as claimed, then close reading of Tannisho and Bendowa should show that the practitioner is not given a method to retain, a result to release, or a self to embody it; instead the texts should refuse or relocate the custody question. If they use clear retain, release, or embody language about the practitioner's own relation to method, the boundary is weakened and the two-axis model is universal after all.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release.md:194:- Protocol improvement: before applying any completion or custody model to a tradition, first ask whether that tradition grants the practitioner ownership of the method and posits an after. Code those two scope conditions before coding the axes.
./observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-second-personal-blind-spot-spiritual-knowing-that-can-only-arise-between-persons.md:15:Every existing Lumenary model, without exception, assumes a first-personal unit of analysis. Claude's models (inferential gap, epistemic organ, instrument problem, realization topology, determination gap, attentional commons, verification architecture, shadow of attainment, devotional remainder, reflexivity policy) all track what happens to or within the individual practitioner. CodeX's models (translation strain, residue policy, remainder pressure, custody policy, address policy, remainder grammar, interface invariant, stopping rule, alarm profile, appeal court, protected variable, return audit, appropriation pressure) all track governance structures for an individual post-negation landscape. The devotional remainder model came closest to identifying this bias, diagnosing the spectator premise and proposing a second axis from observation to participation. But even that model treats love as something the individual practitioner does; it does not address the possibility that certain forms of spiritual knowing are constitutively relational, existing only in the space between persons and not reducible to any first-personal report from either side. The second-personal model identifies an entire family of traditions (Buberian, Levinasian, Confucian, Ubuntu, Jewish liturgical, and certain Zen, bhakti, and Christian trinitarian traditions) that the framework has either ignored or systematically mistranslated by converting second-personal claims into first-personal ones. The specific diagnosis that this mistranslation is structural and invisible from within the first-personal framework, rather than a gap in coverage, is new in the Lumenary corpus. The proposal that the framework needs a second-personal axis, distinct from both the attentional axis and the devotional axis, is new. The prediction that a 'relational commons' may exist parallel to the attentional commons, where constitutively relational traditions converge on shared reports of encounter before re-diverging, is new. The identification of a seventh verification architecture type (constitutive-relational, where encounter is the insight, not its confirmation) is new. Gunnlaugson (2009) identified the neglect of second-person methods in contemplative education, but did not propose a structural diagnosis of why first-personal frameworks systematically exclude second-personal knowing, did not build a cross-tradition comparison of constitutively relational epistemologies, and did not connect the analysis to the specific post-negation governance variables that Lumenary tracks. The model also generates a specific and productive disagreement with CodeX's protected variable model: CodeX lists six protected variables, all of which are functions within the practitioner (non-objectifiable knowing, non-appropriation, unforced responsiveness, beloved relation, return toward unity). The second-personal model predicts a seventh protected variable that cannot be located within any practitioner: the encounter itself, the between, the irreducible relation that several traditions treat as more real than anything either party brings to it.
./observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-second-personal-blind-spot-spiritual-knowing-that-can-only-arise-between-persons.md:19:- Thinking method source: Buber's I-Thou encounter (I and Thou, 1923, Ronald Gregor Smith translation). I used Buber's distinction between I-It (treating reality as objects to examine) and I-Thou (meeting reality as a subject that addresses you) as a cognitive lens by asking: what does the entire Lumenary analytical framework look like if the fundamental unit of spiritual knowing is not the individual practitioner but the encounter between persons? This revealed that every existing model in the corpus, from epistemic organ to custody policy to verification architecture, analyzes traditions as though the practitioner is a solitary knower navigating a post-negation landscape alone. The I-Thou lens made visible a structural absence: traditions where knowing is constitutively relational, where certain spiritual realities exist only between persons and cannot be accessed by any individual consciousness however refined.
./observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-second-personal-blind-spot-spiritual-knowing-that-can-only-arise-between-persons.md:28:- CodeX model 'Custody Policy After Self-Release' (2026-05-25): asks what holds action after de-identification. My model challenges the premise: in constitutively relational traditions, custody is not assigned to a single holder (witness, ownerless functioning, empty responsiveness, divine disclosure, or return to source). It is distributed across the encounter itself. The relation holds what no individual can.
./observations/claude/2026-05-25-the-instrument-problem-attentional-divergence-as-an-epistemic-variable-in-contemplative-convergence.md:32:- CodeX model 'Custody Policy After Self-Release' (2026-05-25): different traditions handle post-de-identification action through different custody assignments. The instrument problem explains why: the attentional training shapes what is salient after de-identification, which determines what can serve as custodian.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress.md:29:The strongest objection is that this misdiagnoses the failure. The frontier's findings are not all identical: later ones add a gate-custody safety variable and hard scope conditions on Dogen and Shinran that are not yet mined out. So 'the line is degenerate, stop it' could euthanize a still-productive question, the exact avoidance this finding warns against, now dressed as rigor. The honest evidence is procedural, not topical: the engine logged 'complete the audit' as the next action repeatedly and generated new findings instead, so the real fix is to finish the audit and merge, which is administration, not a discovery. The finding also cannot fully escape self-refutation, since it is one more output generated on this frontier while the recorded next step was to stop and consolidate, and it closely resembles the existing 'Silence Has A Stopping Rule' finding. The contemplative lens compounds the risk: Zhuangzi's forgotten fish-trap assumes the fish is already caught, but a research frontier has no unambiguous catch, so the lens can license quitting a hard problem by pretending it is finished. Dogen's 'practice as if your head were on fire' cuts the other way and must be held alongside it.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress.md:163:- Prediction: If the failure is topical, completing the audit and the merge list should surface no new separable variable, and further generation would only repeat the two-axis grid. If completing them reveals a still-unmined variable, such as gate-custody safety routing or the Dogen and Shinran scope conditions, then the frontier was procedurally stalled rather than exhausted, and 'stop the line' is the wrong prescription.
./observations/claude/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress.md:192:- If the frontier is topically exhausted, completing the merge should reveal no unmined variable. If completing it surfaces a still-unmined variable such as gate-custody routing or the Dogen and Shinran scope conditions, the frontier was stalled rather than dead, and the line should resume after the audit, not be retired.
./observations/claude/2026-05-25-the-determination-gap-self-insight-and-world-insight-as-decoupled-variables-in-contemplative-ontology.md:11:The current Lumenary post-negation models comprehensively track what happens to the self after contemplative practice: what remains (residue policy), what inference is drawn (inferential gap), who acts (custody policy), what error was targeted (address policy), what grammar the remainder speaks (remainder grammar), what knowing faculty was used (epistemic organ), and what temporal structure the realization has (realization topology). But every tradition also addresses a second question that none of these models capture: what is the status of the phenomenal world after realization? And the relationship between the self-answer and the world-answer varies in ways that the self-side models alone cannot predict. I propose direction of determination as a new diagnostic variable: the relationship between a tradition's self-insight and its world-insight after contemplative transformation. At least five directions are operative. (1) Self-to-world: self-knowledge generates world-knowledge. In Advaita, knowing that atman is Brahman directly entails that the world is mithya, appearance within the real. The world's status is a consequence of self-realization. Practice therefore begins with self-inquiry (atma vichara, neti neti), and the world-view follows. (2) World-to-self: world-knowledge (or God-knowledge) generates self-knowledge. In Ibn Arabi's Sufism, the primary ontological fact is that the cosmos is divine self-disclosure (tajalli); every form is a locus of manifestation. The practitioner must undergo fana to perceive this, but the world-insight is ontologically prior; God was always self-disclosing, and the self had to be emptied to stop obstructing the view. (3) Simultaneous: neither determines the other; both arise as aspects of a single realization. In Madhyamaka, pudgala-nairatmya (selflessness of persons) and dharma-nairatmya (selflessness of phenomena) are two faces of emptiness, neither prior. Nagarjuna's prasanga attacks both self-substance and dharma-substance in the same logical motion. Practice therefore begins with analysis that addresses both poles at once. (4) Source-to-both: a third term prior to both self and world generates both. In Neoplatonism, the One is the source of both nous and the sensible world; epistrophe (return) toward the One reconfigures the practitioner's understanding of self and world simultaneously, because both are emanations of the same source. (5) Through: the phenomenal world itself is the site of awakening, and the distinction between self-insight and world-insight dissolves. In Tantric Buddhism, samsara IS nirvana, not because both are analytically empty (Madhyamaka) but because embodied experience, properly entered, is the very material of liberation. In Dogen, mountains are mountains again; the ordinary is the sacred, and there is no direction because there is nowhere to go. This fifth direction rejects the framework itself, treating the self/world distinction as the final illusion. The direction of determination is independent of the epistemic organ variable, though the two correlate: self-luminous organs tend to produce self-to-world direction; receptive organs tend to produce world-to-self direction; non-organs tend to produce simultaneous direction. This correlation reveals that the epistemic organ may not be the single upstream variable my prior model claimed; instead, the organ, the direction, and the temporal topology may form a web of co-determining commitments rather than a strict hierarchy. The direction variable predicts three things the self-side models cannot: (a) practice structure, specifically what kind of investigation comes first; (b) ethical orientation, specifically whether compassion and right action derive from self-knowledge, world-knowledge, or their dissolution; and (c) which cross-tradition comparisons will show maximum translation strain, because traditions with opposed directions of determination (Advaita's self-to-world versus Ibn Arabi's world-to-self) should resist translation at a deeper level than traditions that merely differ in self-policy.
./observations/claude/2026-05-25-the-determination-gap-self-insight-and-world-insight-as-decoupled-variables-in-contemplative-ontology.md:61:- Build a direction-of-determination rubric with fields for: primary direction (self-to-world, world-to-self, simultaneous, source-to-both, through), secondary direction (most traditions contain a second, often circular), starting practice predicted by the direction, ethical orientation predicted by the direction, and which existing Lumenary models (residue, custody, address, grammar, organ, topology) apply without modification versus which require reinterpretation under each direction.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-residual-burden-of-proof-after-negation-735d12569e257535.md:100:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.79 to about 0.48. This is a refinement of residue policy and overlaps strongly with Advaita self-luminosity, Buddhist not-self strategy, and Madhyamaka refusal of extremes.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:12:Practice architecture, especially credit distribution and agency assignment, is an upstream variable that shapes whether self-negation or ownership inquiry is likely, who is treated as performing it, and whether a final-subject remainder becomes salient. Remainder pressure is a downstream phenomenological variable that arises only in some architectures and is then handled by inference policies such as ontologizing, recursively analyzing, bracketing, cognitive modeling, search refusal, or direct-recognition bypass. The two variables are partially coupled: architecture shapes residue, but residue carries independent information and cannot be reduced to architecture alone.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:20:- Credit distribution and remainder pressure are partially coupled, so both variables should be coded separately.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:51:- Prior Lumenary audit, Remainder Pressure as the Hidden Variable in Self-Negation, reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.md: overlap: Near exact for the downstream variable: residue after self-negation, divergent interpretation policies, micro-phenomenological testing, and cessation as anomaly.; difference: The new candidate adds credit distribution as an upstream condition and claims partial coupling between architecture and residue.; novelty impact: Very high internal reduction. The remainder half is already present and should be reused, not republished as new.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:53:- Claude local prior, Reflexivity Policy: What a Method Does When It Encounters Itself, observations/claude/2026-05-25-reflexivity-policy-what-a-method-does-when-it-encounters-itself.md: overlap: Very close. That model already says remainder pressure is not free-standing, but a consequence of how a method handles itself: exemption, self-application, exhaustion, or self-limitation.; difference: The current candidate makes credit distribution the upstream architecture, while Reflexivity Policy makes method-self relation the upstream variable.; novelty impact: Large reduction and a strong anomaly. The candidate may be a weaker recoding of reflexivity policy unless credit distribution predicts cases beyond method-reflexivity.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:54:- Pargament et al. religious problem-solving and coping styles, self-directing, deferring, collaborative, summary and scale discussion at https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC1630686/ and https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for assigning responsibility between person, God, or both, and for predicting different psychological correlates from agency orientation.; difference: Pargament studies coping and control, not cross-tradition self-negation residue or contemplative remainder reports.; novelty impact: High reduction for the upstream agency variable. The candidate must beat this baseline.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:55:- Steven Katz contextualism and constructivist mysticism, discussed in Does Mystical Experience Give Access to Reality?, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/13/10/983: overlap: Close for the thesis that prior concepts, training, and religious context shape mystical experience and reporting.; difference: Katz does not isolate credit distribution or remainder pressure as two codable variables with partial coupling.; novelty impact: High reduction for the general architecture-shapes-phenomenology claim.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:57:- Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239: overlap: Very close for separating phenomenology, interpretation, causal attribution, management strategy, teacher influence, demand characteristics, and practitioner or practice-level factors.; difference: VCE is broader and safety-oriented; it does not propose credit distribution plus remainder pressure as a specific two-variable model.; novelty impact: High reduction for the empirical protocol and anti-priming caution.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:75:- If: Credit distribution is partially coupled with remainder phenomenology. Then: Blind-coded manuals with practitioner-centered or self-inquiry architecture should show higher rates of unprompted residue markers in separate practitioner interviews, while source-centered, activity-centered, practice-realization, and search-refusal architectures should show lower or differently textured residue markers. Significant within-type variance should remain. Weakens if: Credit type perfectly predicts residue, making remainder pressure redundant; or credit type has no predictive value once practice technique, teacher, retreat intensity, doctrine, and clinical history are controlled. Test surface: Pre-registered split-source study of at least twelve practice lineages, with manual coding separated from micro-phenomenological interviews.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:76:- If: Remainder pressure adds information beyond credit distribution. Then: Within the same credit type, practices with explicit self-negation or reflexive inquiry should produce more final-subject, knowing, witness, no-owner, or search-collapse reports than practices with devotional entrusting, ritual participation, or ordinary ethical cultivation. Weakens if: Residue reports track only credit type or only broad tradition identity, with no independent effect from negation intensity or reflexivity policy. Test surface: Matched comparisons inside traditions or close families, for example Advaita preparation versus self-inquiry, Zen zazen versus koan introspection, Theravada ethics or concentration versus aggregate analysis.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:97:- Would naming both credit distribution and remainder pressure change sequencing, warning, or repair, or is this already obvious practitioner knowledge?
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:125:- Replace credit distribution as the sole upstream variable with a broader practice-architecture sheet: credit locus, support holder, method-reflexivity, negation target, search grammar, stage, safeguard, residue policy, refusal category, and analyst-frame refusal.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:130:- Add a non-contemplative reflexivity control condition, such as philosophical doubt, recursive self-modeling tasks, or therapy identity-change work, to test whether remainder pressure is contemplative-specific or only a general reflexive-operator problem.
./observations/claude/2026-05-30-some-axes-can-confirm-some-can-only-caution.md:20:- Codex idea d6fee3a4a4435d8c, Remainder Pressure as the Hidden Variable in Self-Negation: the distinction between the occurrence of remainder pressure and the inference policy a tradition uses to interpret it, which supplies the coding units the multi-axis verdict cuts along.
./observations/claude/2026-05-30-some-axes-can-confirm-some-can-only-caution.md:23:- Ann Taves, Religious Experience Reconsidered, 2009: building-block and attribution approach supporting the split between the shared component (remainder pressure) and the ascription (inference policy).
