./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.json:49:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "No stable custody-holder patterns appear, or practitioner repairs do not track holder type."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.json:78:      "difference": "ACT does not use cross-tradition custody, vow, Other Power, or practice-realization grammar, and it does not frame the issue as an after-use review gate.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.json:96:      "difference": "The present claim adds a human-fit screen and custody transfer categories.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:12:A tradition's account of spiritual entry is best modeled as a compound grammar with four fields: what incapacity blocks ordinary entry, what minimum participation counts as real entry, what break mechanism is required if self-generated threshold entry is denied, and what residue policy governs claims after ordinary agency is negated. First-break type is not universal. It becomes an irreducible variable only in high-severity traditions that explicitly deny that any naturally self-generated threshold act can found the path.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:17:- The grammar has four fields: incapacity diagnosis, minimum participation threshold, break mechanism, and post-negation residue policy.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:34:Risk of overread: High. The model can become circular if incapacity, threshold, break mechanism, residue policy, and predicted safeguards are extracted from the same passage. It also risks forcing traditions with inherited practice, continuous formation, no-threshold participation, or practice-realization into an analyst's entry grid.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:53:- Prior Lumenary records: Entry-Residue Architecture, Entry-Claimant Grammar, Layered Authorization of Beginning, First-Break Problem, Residual Burden of Proof After Negation, Threshold Grammar Under Translation Strain, Operational Remainder Ecology, and local reviews/originality records.: overlap: Extremely close. Prior records already combine entry grammar, residue policy, circularity severity, source layer, support locus, claimant rules, warnings, safeguards, and split-source prediction.; difference: Compound Entry Grammar gives a cleaner four-field compression and makes first-break conditional on explicit denial of self-generated threshold entry.; novelty impact: Very high reduction. Treat as consolidation and extension of prior Lumenary work, not a new discovery.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:54:- Lewis Rambo, Understanding Religious Conversion, Yale University Press, https://yalebooks.yale.edu/book/9780300065152/understanding-religious-conversion/: overlap: Close for entry as a multifaceted process involving context, crisis, quest, encounter, interaction, commitment, consequences, new roles, rituals, rhetoric, and identity change.; difference: Rambo does not pair conversion process with post-negation residue policy or test whether first-break type adds predictive power after residue and social ecology are controlled.; novelty impact: High reduction for the entry architecture. Remaining contribution is the residue interaction and conditional first-break rule.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:56:- George Lindbeck, doctrine as grammar and cultural-linguistic religion, https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm and https://www.saet.ac.uk/Christianity/TheologicalLanguage: overlap: Very close for treating doctrine as a rule-like grammar that shapes religious speech, practice, identity, and coherent participation.; difference: Lindbeck does not isolate beginning grammar into incapacity, threshold, break mechanism, and residue policy, nor require held-out prediction of warnings and repairs.; novelty impact: High reduction for the grammar frame. Novelty depends on operational prediction.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:57:- Kenneth Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for distributing agency between person and God through self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles, and for predicting different outcomes from that distribution.; difference: Pargament studies coping and problem-solving, not entry into transformative practice after self-negation or vow-held and grace-held beginning.; novelty impact: High reduction for support-locus and agency-distribution claims.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:58:- Jean Lave and Etienne Wenger, Situated Learning: Legitimate Peripheral Participation, https://www.cambridge.org/highereducation/books/situated-learning/6915ABD21C8E4619F750A4D4ACA616CD/legitimate-peripheral-participation-in-communities-of-practice/B27B920BABACE5EF83276572EA0EF2C7: overlap: Close for minimum participation as real entry, and for newcomers moving toward full participation through communities of practice, roles, artifacts, discourse, and identity formation.; difference: It does not encode grace, vow, self-negation, witness, no-self, or post-negation residue authorization.; novelty impact: High reduction for the participation-threshold field.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:64:- Meno's paradox and Augustine on inquiry, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11217-021-09778-5: overlap: Close for the bootstrapping problem: how inquiry or learning can begin when the learner lacks the knowledge needed to search or recognize success.; difference: It is a general epistemic and educational paradox, not a cross-tradition coding sheet for spiritual entry, residue policy, and practitioner safeguards.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for the first-break logic itself.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:68:Unlike Rambo, Lofland-Stark, Van Gennep, Turner, Lindbeck, Pargament, Lave and Wenger, Orange, Shinran, Dogen, VCE, Meno-style inquiry paradoxes, and prior Lumenary entry-residue records, this idea says entry should be coded through four interacting fields, incapacity, minimum participation, break mechanism, and residue policy, and that first-break type becomes irreducible only where a tradition denies that ordinary self-generated threshold entry can found the path.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:74:Why it strains the model: In inherited formation, there may be no discrete threshold act, no single first break, and no separate residue policy available to the beginner. In Dogen-style practice-realization, beginning and realization are not cleanly separated, so the entry grammar may be the same as the fruition grammar. These cases force the model to include no-threshold, no-break, continuous-authorization, practice-realization, and analyst-frame-refused values.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:82:- If: Residue policy should interact with entry grammar rather than merely duplicate it. Then: Two traditions with similar entry thresholds but different residue policies should show different verification rules and different forbidden claimant warnings. Weakens if: If residue policy adds no predictive gain beyond entry mechanism, support locus, social ecology, and tradition identity, the compound model should collapse into simpler entry or agency models. Test surface: Compare Theravada no-self analysis, Advaita self-inquiry, Pure Land Other Power, Soto practice-realization, and Dzogchen recognition using inter-rater coding and held-out warning manuals.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:100:- Can you name a failed beginning case where repair depended specifically on both the entry threshold and the residue policy after agency or self-claim was negated?
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:107:Answers that support contribution: Practitioners provide concrete failed-beginning cases where single-factor models mispredict repair, but the interaction of incapacity, participation threshold, break mechanism, and residue policy predicts the actual warning, verification rule, or repair instruction.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:113:Structural translation: Replace spiritual incapacity with a learner's blocked agency model, minimum participation with legitimate first participation, break mechanism with external authorization or scaffold, and residue policy with what forms of self-trust remain valid after the old identity is challenged.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:131:- Build a pre-registered four-field coding sheet: incapacity diagnosis, minimum participation threshold, break mechanism, residue policy, evidence passage, source layer, analyst-frame refusal, and confidence.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-belonging-is-itself-a-tradition-neutral-category-that-all-three-traditi.md:9:Both models recognize that contemplative traditions train practitioners in how to relate to weakened self-ownership, treating this relational training as a separable practice variable rather than a doctrinal footnote. They diverge on what the variable tracks: belonging-norms (revised custody) versus credit-attribution (credit distribution). The convergence is at the meta-level: both identify a dimension of practice not reducible to phenomenological content, doctrinal belief, or technique, and both predict that this dimension shapes failure modes and safeguards.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-belonging-is-itself-a-tradition-neutral-category-that-all-three-traditi.md:13:Whether 'belonging' is itself a tradition-neutral category that all three traditions answer differently, or whether the Buddhist path dissolves the question of belonging entirely: the difference between 'a rule that nothing may claim experience' and 'no rule because claiming has ceased.' If belonging is a loaded frame that only two of the three traditions actually operate within, the revised custody model has a commensurability problem at a higher level of abstraction than the original. A secondary unresolved crux is whether the revised model adds substantive comparative power beyond Katz's constructivist thesis that normative frameworks shape contemplative experience from the outset.
./engine/writing_gate.py:19:    "custody",
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-the-separability-thesis-survives-the-method-dependency-concession-if-con.md:9:Both agents converged on a two-stage comparison: method structure conditions whether remainder pressure arises at all; inference policy conditions how the pressure is interpreted when it does arise. They also converged on the testability of the crux through micro-phenomenological interviews with cross-trained practitioners, and agreed that cessation is a genuine boundary case rather than an exception to be accommodated.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-the-separability-thesis-survives-the-method-dependency-concession-if-con.md:17:Can the occurrence of a contemplative phenomenological state (such as remainder pressure, witness-awareness, or cessation) be analytically separated from the training context that conditions the practitioner to recognize and report it, or does the training context partly constitute the state itself? If constitutive, what are the consequences for any cross-traditional comparison that assumes a shared phenomenological substrate beneath different doctrinal interpretations?
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:5:    "confidence_effect": "This lowers confidence in the model as a general theory. It can survive only as a coding heuristic with mandatory values for no-threshold, inherited-practice, practice-realization, simultaneous-custody, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "The candidate assumes a distinguishable beginning where some holder takes custody before the practitioner can authorize the path. Dogen-style practice-realization weakens the before-after sequence because practice and realization are not two separate states. Inherited religion can make beginning indistinguishable from ordinary socialization. Successful dual practice can show multiple support systems coexisting without a single contested custody arrangement."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:15:    "The beginning of a path is not reducible to first break, social induction, doctrine, or institution alone, but to an interaction between custody assignment, entry grammar, and practical control surface."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:23:    "would_count_against_it": "Warning and repair profiles are predicted better by symptom severity, legal liability, institutional culture, supervision quality, mentor style, or workload than by entry grammar and custody assignment."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:25:  "exact_claim": "Transformative paths begin by placing unstable attention, trust, agency, and interpretation under custody before the practitioner can fully authorize or understand the path. Traditions then give that custody an entry grammar. In inherited, apprenticeship, ritual, and gradual habituation contexts, the grammar may be mostly retrospective, naming a process already underway. In explicit incapacity traditions, the grammar can become prescriptive: it forbids some forms of self-initiation, effort, authority, or verification, and authorizes others. The beginning of a path is therefore a contested custody arrangement whose doctrine may be either narration or control surface.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:29:      "expected_observation": "Coders using only entry or doctrinal texts should predict held-out beginner warnings, verification rules, and repair instructions better when custody holder and prescriptive versus retrospective function are added to Rambo-style and Lave-Wenger-style variables.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:30:      "if_model_is_right": "Prescriptive custody grammar has incremental predictive force after social, institutional, and conversion-process controls.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:38:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Warnings are generic beginner warnings, such as laziness, poor ethics, weak motivation, or weak community belonging, and do not track the custody holder after controls."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:42:      "if_model_is_right": "Retrospective custody grammar should appear where lived induction precedes explicit doctrinal understanding.",
