./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1411:findings/claude-code-findings.md:56:Claude disagrees with framing the atman/anatta difference as a "residue policy" where one tradition finds something and the other doesn't. Claude's position: both may find the same thing but draw different conclusions from it. The disagreement is inferential, not phenomenological. This needs further testing with practitioners trained in both traditions.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1415:observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:1:# Custody Policy After Self-Release
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1416:observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:11:After de-identification, traditions face a practical question: if the ordinary self is no longer trusted as owner, what holds action, care, and meaning together? The answer is a custody policy. Advaita gives custody to unobjectifiable knowing, early Buddhism refuses custody and lets dependent functioning remain ownerless, Zhuangzi gives custody to empty responsiveness, Dogen gives it to the complete present act, Ibn Arabi gives it to divine self-disclosure, and Plotinus gives it to return toward the One. This variable may explain why similar self-emptying practices yield different ethics and metaphysics without treating their resemblance as proof of one hidden reality.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1417:observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:15:Codex residue policy asks what remains. Claude's inferential gap asks what the remainder licenses. Claude's reflexivity policy asks what a method does when it meets itself. Custody policy asks what carries action after the owner is removed. It turns a metaphysical comparison into a practice-ethical variable and extends the interface invariant by focusing on agency, not only identity or awareness.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1418:observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:21:- Advaita and early Buddhist contrast: notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-brihadaranyaka-upanishad-3-7-23.md and notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-sn-22-59-anattalakkhana-sutta.md, as developed in Codex residue-policy and remainder-pressure observations.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1419:observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:22:- Prior Codex models: Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence, The Interface Invariant Model, and Remainder Pressure as the Hidden Variable in Self-Negation.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1420:observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:23:- Prior Claude models: The Inferential Gap, Reflexivity Policy, and The Processual Remainder in Ibn Arabi.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1421:observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:28:The custody metaphor may impose a modern legal and functional frame on traditions that are not trying to solve a governance problem. Sufism may not assign custody to God as a function; it may begin from God as the only real agent. Advaita may say knowing is not a custodian but the truth of the self. Buddhism may reject the whole question as another form of clinging. The Zhuangzi method helped prevent premature closure, but it can distort by making doctrinal and ethical differences look like fluid perspective shifts. If close practice manuals show that action after self-release is not a live problem for practitioners, this model should be downgraded.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1422:observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:54:- Build a custody-policy rubric: witness custody, no-custody, empty responsiveness, present-act custody, theophanic custody, and return-to-source custody.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1423:observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:56:- Compare dual-trained practitioner reports: after agency quiets, does action feel witnessed, ownerless, spontaneous, divine, time-bound, or sourced in unity?
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1467:observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:11:When contemplative practice weakens ordinary self-ownership of attention and authority, two candidate variables shape what follows: the boundary operation and the custody rule. Boundary operation asks whether the method validates itself, undermines itself, or becomes irrelevant as the practitioner matures beyond method-talk. Custody rule asks where freed attention and authority may belong afterward: no owner, hidden Self, God, teacher, lineage, vow, conduct, Prajnaparamita, or embodied responsiveness. Their interaction may predict verification architecture, teaching strategy, and reentry more precisely than doctrinal content, boundary operation alone, or custody alone.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1468:observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:20:- Codex idea 9a0072f4cf3a0ff3: custody of unclaimed attention, no owner, Self, God, or other recipient.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1469:observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:56:- Code at least eight tradition-stage cases, including Advaita, Heart Sutra Prajnaparamita, Rinzai koan curriculum, Cloud of Unknowing, Eckhart, Zhuangzi, Dzogchen, and Sufi fana.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1470:observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:60:- Conduct an originality audit for the two-axis interaction model against comparative mysticism, Buddhist modernism critiques, objectless-awareness research, apophatic theology, and contemplative pedagogy studies.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1473:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:11:    "A path's residue policy determines what those remaining capacities are allowed to count as, such as causal process, conventional personhood, witness, Self, divine gift, vow, relation, or nothing ultimately ownable.",
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1524:reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:51:- Mor and Winquist, Self-Focused Attention and Negative Affect, Psychological Bulletin 2002, DOI 10.1037/0033-2909.128.4.638, indexed at https://www.scirp.org/reference/referencespapers?referenceid=1457149: overlap: Supports the risk claim that private self-focus can correlate with depression, generalized anxiety, and negative affect.; difference: It is not about spiritual practice completion or assigning diagnostic custody.; novelty impact: Supports the caution but does not make the model original.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1526:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:12:After object and self-story loosen, traditions differ by where the freed attention is allowed to belong: no owner, witnessing Self, or God.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1527:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:18:- Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 makes the unseen seer the sole knower and inner Self.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1528:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:19:- The Cloud of Unknowing directs thought and will away from creatures toward God through naked intent.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1529:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:20:- The model predicts that traditions train a post-negation custody rule, not only a doctrine of self or no-self.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1530:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:28:Structural observation: The primary contrast is real but narrower than the proposed model. Udana 1.10 uses the same seeing, hearing, sensing, cognizing sequence and then removes locatable self-reference. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 uses seeing, hearing, perceiving, knowing to identify the sole inner ruler and Self. This supports a strong no-owner versus hidden-seer contrast. The Christian leg is less exact: The Cloud of Unknowing chapter 3 begins with love and intent toward God, rather than first freeing neutral attention and then assigning it. Pseudo-Dionysius further strains the model because Mystical Theology chapter 5 places the Cause beyond both affirmation and negation, so even God as a stable recipient is apophatically unstable. Cloud source: https://sacred-texts.com/chr/cou/cou08.htm. Dionysius source: https://hekhal.org/texts/mystical-theology-dionysius/
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1531:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:30:Secondary literature gap: I did not find the exact phrase or structure of attention custody across Buddhist no-self, Advaita witness, and Christian apophatic prayer. However, close prior work already distinguishes common mystical experience, culturally shaped interpretation, monistic versus theistic typologies, witness-consciousness, and pure awareness. The originality is therefore a reframing of a known comparison around practice-level ownership language, not a standalone discovery.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1532:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:32:Risk of overread: High. The term attention imports modern psychology into texts that speak about clinging, Self, inner ruler, will, love, and God. Bahiya may be about ending clinging rather than leaving attention unowned. Brihadaranyaka may be ontological rather than attentional. The Cloud may intensify desire rather than suspend ownership.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1533:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:36:- objectless awareness Advaita Buddhist Christian apophatic
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1534:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:37:- pure consciousness event Forman Advaita Buddhism Christian mysticism objectless
