./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1536:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:39:- Fasching I Am of the Nature of Seeing witness-consciousness Buddhist Advaita
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1537:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:40:- pure awareness experience Ramm 2023 witness consciousness selfless
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1538:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:41:- minimal phenomenal experience objectless selfless awareness Buddhist Advaita
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1539:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:46:- Robert K. C. Forman, Mysticism, Mind, Consciousness, Google Books page, https://books.google.com/books/about/Mysticism_Mind_Consciousness.html?id=I28wCczdcpEC: overlap: Forman's pure consciousness event and dualistic mystical state compare objectless or nonintentional awareness across Indian, Chinese, medieval European, and modern accounts.; difference: Forman tends to argue for direct encounter with consciousness itself, while this idea emphasizes divergent custodians of attention after ordinary ownership weakens.; novelty impact: High reduction. Forman already frames the central terrain as contentless consciousness plus interpretive difference.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1540:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:47:- Wolfgang Fasching, I Am of the Nature of Seeing: Phenomenological Reflections on the Indian Notion of Witness-Consciousness, PhilPapers, https://philpapers.org/rec/FASIAO-5: overlap: Gives a close Advaita account of witness-consciousness as the abiding dimension in which changing experiences appear, directly overlapping the hidden-seer custody leg.; difference: Does not triangulate with Bahiya's no-location instruction or Christian apophatic love.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. One major unit of the model is already well articulated.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1541:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:49:- Michael A. Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying, University of Chicago Press, https://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/M/bo3635525.html: overlap: Shows apophatic language turning back on its own propositions and names across Greek, Christian, and Islamic texts, close to the Christian unknowing side.; difference: Sells analyzes apophatic discourse and its paradoxes, not attention ownership across Buddhist, Advaita, and Christian practices.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. It makes the Christian leg less new and highlights the Dionysian anomaly.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1542:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:53:Unlike common-core or constructivist accounts, this idea says the decisive variable is not only whether an experience is the same or differently interpreted, but whether training assigns loosened attention to no owner, the witnessing Self, or God.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1543:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:65:- If: Practitioners trained in Bahiya-style sense instruction, Advaita self-inquiry, and Christian apophatic prayer should diverge most in ownership and recipient language at the moment ordinary self-reference drops. Then: Interview transcripts should cluster around no one there, witnessing Self, and God or beloved as recipient, even when sensory content and quietness descriptions overlap. Weakens if: Reports cluster only by phenomenological texture, emotional tone, or teacher charisma, with no stable ownership or recipient pattern. Test surface: Micro-phenomenological interviews with trained Theravada, Advaita, and apophatic practitioners.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1544:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:66:- If: Changing the instruction at the handoff point should change later interpretation more than immediate perceptual content. Then: A practitioner given no-location language, witness language, or God-directed language after similar objectless calm should later describe different belonging or authorization, while reporting similar quiet or contentlessness. Weakens if: The initial phenomenology changes before doctrinal instruction, or the ownership language remains random after instruction. Test surface: Controlled meditation instruction study with post-session interview coding.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1545:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:67:- If: Primary manuals should contain explicit or implicit custody rules near passages that loosen ordinary selfing. Then: Texts should pair negation of objects or self-story with instructions such as do not locate a self, know the unseen seer, or lift the heart to God. Weakens if: The relevant manuals loosen objects without any subsequent owner, Self, or recipient language, or use all three interchangeably. Test surface: Close-reading corpus of Theravada, Advaita, Christian apophatic, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra manuals.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1546:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:85:Answers that support contribution: Practitioners independently identify a decisive handoff point and report that no-owner, witness, and God-directed instructions change practice understanding.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1547:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:91:Structural translation: De-identification practices loosen ordinary ownership of thoughts, then assign the released stance to no-self mindfulness, observing self, values, therapist relationship, or a higher power.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1548:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:103:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.72 to about 0.58. The custody phrase appears fresh, but the structure sits close to established work on pure consciousness, constructivism, theistic versus monistic typologies, witness-consciousness, and apophasis.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1554:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:51:- Prior Lumenary audit, Remainder Pressure as the Hidden Variable in Self-Negation, reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.md: overlap: Near exact for the downstream variable: residue after self-negation, divergent interpretation policies, micro-phenomenological testing, and cessation as anomaly.; difference: The new candidate adds credit distribution as an upstream condition and claims partial coupling between architecture and residue.; novelty impact: Very high internal reduction. The remainder half is already present and should be reused, not republished as new.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1557:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:76:- If: Remainder pressure adds information beyond credit distribution. Then: Within the same credit type, practices with explicit self-negation or reflexive inquiry should produce more final-subject, knowing, witness, no-owner, or search-collapse reports than practices with devotional entrusting, ritual participation, or ordinary ethical cultivation. Weakens if: Residue reports track only credit type or only broad tradition identity, with no independent effect from negation intensity or reflexivity policy. Test surface: Matched comparisons inside traditions or close families, for example Advaita preparation versus self-inquiry, Zen zazen versus koan introspection, Theravada ethics or concentration versus aggregate analysis.
