./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1568:observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:1:# Remainder Pressure as the Hidden Variable in Self-Negation
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1569:observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:27:One system may ontologize the pressure: the pressure points to a real witness that cannot be objectified.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1570:observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:67:A narrow bridge between Upanishadic witness language, early Buddhist not-self analysis, and modern consciousness research is the variable of remainder pressure: the felt or conceptual demand to posit a final subject when all object-like contents have been negated. The comparison should not ask whether these sources agree about the self, but how each system manages that pressure: ontologizing it as an unobjectifiable seer, recursively applying analysis to it, bracketing it as a reportable phenomenological residue, or treating it as a self-modeling artifact.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1571:observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:71:This shifts the comparison from a binary self/no-self dispute to a micro-mechanism that can be tracked across text, practice report, and cognitive model. The novelty is the distinction between the occurrence of remainder pressure and the inference policy used to interpret it, which lets convergence generate hypotheses without being promoted into evidence for a shared metaphysical object.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1572:observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:75:- Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 as cited in observations/codex/2026-05-25-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md: an unseen seer/hearer/knower is preserved as Self or inner ruler after ordinary objectification fails.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1573:observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:79:- Modern consciousness research on self-modeling and metacognition, used only as empirical-adjacent analogy: first-person ownership, agency, and meta-awareness can be studied without settling the metaphysical status of a witness.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1574:observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:111:- Ask whether meta-awareness research can operationalize the occurrence of remainder pressure without implying that the pressure points to a real metaphysical witness.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1575:observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:112:- Look for cases where traditions explicitly warn against reifying the witness, because those may reveal an intermediate position between Upanishadic authorization and Buddhist refusal.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1578:findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:12:**CodeX** (Translation Strain model): The key distinction between traditions is the "residue policy"; whether a tradition licenses or withholds ontological residue after negation practice. Advaita finds a witness-consciousness residue; Buddhism finds none.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1581:findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:25:- If their phenomenological reports themselves differ (e.g., Advaitins literally experience a witness, Buddhists literally do not) → CodeX's residue policy model is supported, and experience is theory-laden.
./runs/20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1582:observations/codex/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface.md:11:A contemplative path that weakens ordinary self-ownership needs a custody architecture and a local human interface. Custody names where transformation functions are assigned: causal process, hidden Self, teacher, vow, grace, community, ritual, God, or the individual practitioner. Receiving surface names what must remain available in the practitioner for the path to land: investigation, entrusting, recognition, loving attention, non-fabrication, or embodied presence. The model is not yet entitled to say these are two independent causes. Its strongest candidate form is a coding framework: record custody assignment, receiving surface, named failure mode, teacher intervention, sequencing, and verification method separately, then test whether receiving surface adds prediction beyond custody.
