observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger.md:28:The synthesis may become too elaborate to compress the phenomena it studies. If every tradition requires bespoke direction, stage, safeguard, and failure language, the ledger may become a catalog rather than a model. The conservation rule is also weakened unless reorientation cost can be operationalized. Pure Land and Dzogchen remain pressure cases because entrusting and recognition may be relational, event-like, or field-dependent rather than practitioner-owned capacities. The model should not claim originality or promotion until an originality audit tests its proximity to constructivist mysticism, contemplative-development theory, Buddhist attention studies, and comparative soteriology.
reviews/human-condition/audits.jsonl:9:{"agent": "claude", "audit_id": "4fb20766c6877b0d", "caution": "Do not turn metaphysical uncertainty into pressure to dissolve the person faster than life can safely hold.", "confidence": 0.78, "created_at": "2026-05-26T18:12:02-07:00", "execution_id": "human-condition-backfill-20260526-finding-style-fix", "fit_status": "direct", "idea_id": "b9b51fb9d8104a8e", "keywords_matched": ["self", "atman", "anatta", "consciousness", "negation", "remainder", "meaning"], "next_question": "What must remain intact for this insight to make life more honest rather than more empty?", "non_fit": "Not enough for dissociation, psychosis, suicidal crisis, or any state where self-inquiry increases instability.", "practical_implication": "A practice derived from this finding should name what must remain after letting go: care, memory, responsibility, or simple awareness.", "primary_problem": "Meaning loss, identity confusion, and the danger of using self-negation in a way that leaves a person unmoored.", "run_ids": ["human-condition-backfill-20260526-finding-style-fix"], "source_card_ids": ["modern-human-condition-pew-where-americans-find-meaning-in-life", "modern-human-condition-who-world-mental-health-report", "modern-human-condition-cdc-suicide-facts"], "target_cohort": "People asking who they are, what remains when old identities fall away, or how to loosen ego without losing care and responsibility.", "title": "Expressive Realism: Dogen's Being-Time as a Dissolution of the Passage Problem That Neither Eternalism Nor Presentism Can Resolve", "why_it_matters": "It can protect deep inquiry from becoming vague self-erasure or a new hidden ego claim."}
