reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:165:    "structural_observation": "The close read supports a broader architecture variable, but not credit distribution alone. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 asserts an inner seer and knower through a cosmological inner-ruler grammar; it does not show a reported pressure after practice. SN 22.59 applies an ownership and control test to all aggregates and ends in disenchantment, dispassion, release, and knowledge of release; it does not leave a witness as the text's authorized remainder. Huangbo strains the sequence because it rejects using mind to seek Mind and treats objectified seeking itself as the mistake. Dogen strains it differently: practice and realization are one, so the cause-result and claimant sequence is collapsed rather than managed downstream. These sources suggest that method-reflexivity, search grammar, and practice-realization may be as upstream as credit distribution."
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:19:- Thinking method source: Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/. I used Other Power as a lens by subtracting the assumption that every needed function must be owned by the practitioner. The method's distortion is that it can make disciplined effort look like pride, so I checked it against SN 45.8 on right effort.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:20:- Primary close-reading: SN 45.8 Magga-Vibhanga Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN45_8.html, against Shinran's Letter to Senshin. SN 45.8 authorizes generated desire, persistence, intent, prevention, abandonment, cultivation, and maintenance. Shinran forbids calculation on the practicer's side. The comparison reveals that function and claimant must be separated.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:22:- Primary close-reading: Dogen, Bendowa, Kazuaki Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/. Dogen says the dharma is abundant in each person yet not actualized without practice, and that practice and realization cannot be recognized as two separate things. This makes the present act a support locus while forbidding future-gaining ownership.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:24:- Near-neighbor search: Jack Engler, You Must Be Somebody Before You Can Be Nobody, https://inquiringmind.com/article/0501_1_engler-interview/; Bhikkhu Analayo, Skill in Means and Mindfulness, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12671-021-01795-2; Harvard Divinity Bulletin on Buddhist skillful means, https://bulletin.hds.harvard.edu/buddhist-studies-the-buddhist-way/. These sources cover ego strength, capacity-sensitive teaching, and pedagogical adaptation, but not a two-part code of support locus plus forbidden claimant across effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:30:The strongest counterexample is Chinul's sudden awakening and gradual cultivation. In Secrets on Cultivating the Mind, awakening is sudden, later cultivation is necessary, and true cultivation eliminates without treating anything as truly eliminated. The same action can be authorized or forbidden depending on whether it relies on awakening or on goal-seeking delusion. That may make the rubric too stage-dependent to remain clean. Radical Jodo Shinshu adds a sharper theological objection: if true entrusting is Amida's working, even calling the vow a support locus may still be an outside analyst's way of domesticating grace. The Shinran lens also biases the analysis toward ownership suspicion; right effort corrects this by showing that desire, effort, and maintenance can be medicines rather than theft. The model should be weakened if primary manuals do not show recurring wrong-claimant warnings, or if practitioners say ownership language is alien to their actual training.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:59:- If this model is right, then adverse contemplative events should cluster around wrong-claimant failures: self-power anxiety in gift practice, achievement seeking in practice-realization, reification after direct introduction, and mechanical striving in effort practice. If adverse reports do not vary by claimant pattern after controlling for trauma, intensity, and supervision, the model is weakened.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen-style practice-realization, inherited communal practice, and radical Other Power cases where the analyst cannot cleanly separate custody, entry, and receiving surface.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:5:    "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence from candidate discovery to extended. The model needs analyst-frame-refused, no-threshold, inherited-practice, practice-realization, radical-other-power, and undecidable values before use.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If practice and realization are nondual, there may be no discrete landing event and no separate receiving surface. If a person is gradually formed by inherited communal participation before explicit assent, the receiving surface may be socialized rather than locally chosen. If radical Other Power refuses any self-power residue, calling entrusting a human surface may distort the doctrine by reintroducing the agency it rejects."
