reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:163:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with shikantaza and practice-realization",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:169:      "Tannisho, BDK translation, especially chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, 11 and Rennyo postscript, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:172:      "Dogen, Bendowa practice-realization sources, for anomaly pressure, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:175:    "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit used accessible translations and open academic or practitioner-facing sources. It did not fully close-read Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, Dzogchen or Mahamudra manuals, John of the Cross, Teresa of Avila, Christian grace controversy sources, or Sanskrit, Pali, Japanese, Tibetan, and Latin originals. It also did not run practitioner interviews. Novelty should not rise without split-source coding and interview evidence.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:176:    "structural_observation": "Tannisho strongly supports vow-held custody: Amida's vow carries salvific efficacy and self-power calculation is treated as deviation. Yet it still requires hearing, entrusting, teacher lineage, and restricted readiness, so a receiving surface remains visible. SN 22.59 negates ownership and mastery over the aggregates, but the discourse still depends on instruction, discernment, memory, and seeing with right understanding, so causal-process custody does not eliminate local investigation. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 gives the opposite residue policy: ordinary objectification fails, but the hidden knower or inner controller is authorized as the remainder. Dogen's practice-realization strains the model because practice and realization are not cleanly separable stages, making custody and receiving surface look like an analyst-imposed split. These primary texts support the distinction as a useful coding question, but not as a proven independent structure."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json:185:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament's agency styles, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Asad's discursive tradition, VCE adverse-effects research, upaya capacity pedagogy, Pure Land Other Power, Christian attention and grace theology, pointing-out instruction, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says that the assigned holder of transformation and the practitioner's required mode of availability should be coded separately, then tested to see whether the second variable predicts warnings, sequencing, teacher repairs, and verification beyond the first."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:18:- Different primary texts model different endings: MN 22 releases the raft after right use, Heart Sutra negates attainment while retaining reliance, Mandukya allows a known Self, Rinzai koan work exhausts ordinary thinking while remaining curriculum, and Dogen collapses before and after through practice-realization.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:29:Structural observation: MN 22 is a close primary near-neighbor for validated-then-released method. It teaches right grasp, crossing, and release of the raft, so the candidate's set-down category is old. The Heart Sutra complicates the model because it negates attainment yet retains reliance on Prajnaparamita and mantra. This supports the candidate's claim that undermining result does not always mean abandoning method. Mandukya adds a different pressure: negation culminates in the Self that is to be known. Dogen strains the whole after-completion frame because practice and realization are inseparable, so return is not a later test but the practice itself.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:33:Risk of overread: High. The model may impose a modern performance and safety rubric on traditions whose own test is surrender, grace, vow, direct recognition, ritual continuity, or inherited participation. It may also moralize return to productivity in a way that worsens burnout if ordinary conduct is confused with more output.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:41:- "Dogen" "practice and realization are one" Bendowa
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:48:- Dogen Bendowa material, Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/: overlap: Close anomaly and near-neighbor. Dogen's practice-realization already says practice is not a means to a later result and realization is not an object privately recognized after practice.; difference: The candidate makes Dogen an anomaly inside a return model, whereas Dogen may reject the whole before, peak, after sequence.; novelty impact: Lowers confidence. If Dogen is central rather than marginal, the return test may be only an external heuristic.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:56:Unlike the raft simile, apophatic unsaying, therapeutic readings of Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Dogen practice-realization, VCE aftercare, Asad's discursive tradition, and Lindbeck's doctrine grammar, this idea's distinct claim is a practical comparative test: code whether a method validates or undermines the result, then code whether the method is retained, released, or embodied, and see whether that interaction predicts warnings, re-entry duties, identity risks, and repairs better than doctrine, institution, teacher style, or clinical-risk variables alone.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:60:Candidate: Dogen practice-realization, radical Other Power in Tannisho, inherited communal religion, and successful ordinary ethical practice without a marked peak experience.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:62:Why it strains the model: These cases resist the sequence of method, result, and return. Dogen makes practice and realization inseparable. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Vow and can make nembutsu non-practice from the practitioner's side. Inherited religion may not have a discrete completion event. Ordinary ethical formation may return without peak experience at all.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:64:Confidence effect: Prevents candidate-discovery status. The model is useful as a heuristic only if it can code no-threshold, no-peak, Other Power, inherited practice, and practice-realization without forcing them into a modern after-experience frame.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:70:- If: Cross-training will expose different return grammars. Then: Practitioners trained in Advaita inquiry, Prajnaparamita practice, raft-style early Buddhist training, and Soto practice-realization will describe different appropriate relations to insight: stable recognition, resisted attainment, released tool, or ongoing practice-conduct identity. Weakens if: Practitioners converge on the same return rule after controlling for teacher and personality, or differences reduce to vocabulary without behavioral, warning, or repair consequences. Test surface: Dual-trained practitioner interviews and behavior-coded follow-up after comparable retreat experiences.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:76:- Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization and Rinzai koan curriculum
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:79:- Jodo Shinshu teachers familiar with Tannisho and Other Power
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:88:Answers that reduce originality: Teachers recognize the rubric as ordinary raft teaching, upaya, practice-realization, apophatic unsaying, koan curriculum, spiritual exercise, aftercare, or ethics of fruits, and say it does not predict guidance beyond existing lineage rules.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:108:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.58 to 0.41. The teaching line is strong and publishable only as a restrained synthesis for achievement-contingent self-worth. The research model should be treated as extended prior art until it predicts warnings, repairs, or return duties better than existing upaya, raft, apophatic, practice-realization, spiritual-exercises, VCE, authority, and grammar frameworks.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:114:- Add mandatory anomaly values for practice-realization, radical Other Power, inherited religion, no-threshold practice, no-peak ethical formation, direct recognition, and clinician-held support.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:116:- Close-read Tannisho, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, a Rinzai koan curriculum source, Cloud of Unknowing or Dionysius, a Dzogchen pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before raising source reliability.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-making-silence-judge-you-426c0c34cd74415c.md:33:Risk of overread: Very high if generalized. Advaita, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, clear-light sleep, and direct-recognition lineages may treat some quiet or objectless reports as trainable evidence within strict contexts. In OCD, scrupulosity, trauma, dissociation, mania, severe depression, and unsafe authority settings, the instruction can become avoidance, checking, reassurance outsourcing, or control.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-making-silence-judge-you-426c0c34cd74415c.md:78:- Advaita, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, and sleep-yoga teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-making-silence-judge-you-426c0c34cd74415c.md:120:- Add a direct-recognition anomaly set before public use: Advaita, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, clear-light sleep, and competent teacher-held recognition.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface.md:15:The source ideas already contained minimum-self architecture and custody-of-attention, but the dialogue created a distinct comparative object: the interface between assigned custody and practitioner receptivity. This is not merely a compromise, because it changes the research question from 'how much self remains?' or 'where does attention belong?' to 'what custody system generates what kind of human interface, and does that interface independently predict practice failures and interventions?' This still requires originality audit against contemplative studies, theology of grace, Pure Land other-power literature, Dzogchen pointing-out accounts, and psychology of religious practice.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface.md:57:- Test Shin Buddhism, Christian infused contemplation, Dzogchen pointing-out, Theravada insight practice, and Advaita self-inquiry as initial cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:58:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization zazen primary text"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:147:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with practice-realization",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:148:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:158:      "Dogen, Bendowa, Tanahashi translation excerpt and commentary, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-1-of-3/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:162:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 presents path factors as trainable functions, including right view, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. Dogen's Bendowa makes zazen not merely one transferable technique but the expression of the Way itself, where practice and realization are not cleanly separated. The pair supports the candidate's distinction between repeated operation and practice grammar. Similar sitting or effort can have different meaning, authority, and endpoint structures."
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:11:A path should be compared in two ordered layers. First, identify the register in which the tradition locates decisive transformation: human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, divine restoration, causal continuity, or another account. Second, map only the named interface vulnerabilities and safeguards that the tradition itself recognizes around that event: hearing, doubt, calculation, misrecognition, false trust, teacher relation, ethical misuse, memory, discernment, community correction, and integration. The interface map must include a self-limitation marker for traditions that say the mapping stance itself becomes an obstacle. Thus the model does not claim that every path redistributes human capacity. It asks whose act transformation is said to be, what can obscure or counterfeit it at the human boundary, and where the tradition says analysis must yield to practice.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:23:- Dialogue turn 3 reflexive objection from Shinran's jinen honi and the need for self-limitation
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:56:- Ask Jodo Shinshu and Dzogchen teachers whether register-sensitive interface mapping avoids self-power or psychological distortion, or whether even this second-order mapping remains misleading.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:58:- Test whether the model predicts warning profiles in manuals before reading their warnings. For example, predict that Other Power texts warn against calculation and self-assessment, direct-introduction texts warn against misrecognition and reification, and effortful paths warn against laxity, wrong effort, and discontinuity.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen's practice-realization and other no-boundary traditions where decisive transformation is not approached through a separable practitioner-event interface.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:5:    "confidence_effect": "This lowers originality and model confidence. The idea remains useful as a careful comparative heuristic, but it should be classed as extended unless it replaces interface with coding values such as no-boundary, collapsed-boundary, practice-realization, vow-mediated, teacher-mediated, and analyst-frame-refused.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:10:    "Comparison must first preserve the transformation register, such as human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, divine restoration, or causal continuity.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:28:      "expected_observation": "Tannisho, Shinran letters, and Jodo Shinshu teaching materials should warn more against self-power, calculation, pride in practice, and self-assessment than against laxity as the primary danger.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:29:      "if_model_is_right": "Other Power texts should show a distinctive warning profile after the register is identified.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:31:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Other Power materials do not warn against calculation more than effort-centered manuals, or the warnings track genre, polemic, or institution better than transformation register."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:34:      "expected_observation": "Dzogchen and Mahamudra materials should warn especially against misrecognition, mistaking an experience for recognition, reifying awareness, inadequate teacher relation, and failure to integrate conduct.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:35:      "if_model_is_right": "Direct-introduction traditions should show a warning profile distinct from Other Power traditions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:40:      "expected_observation": "Dogen and Soto materials should correct before-after, means-end, and practitioner-event separations more often than texts framed by gradual effort, vow, grace, or recognition.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:42:      "test_surface": "Bendowa, Genjokoan, selected Shobogenzo fascicles, Soto practice manuals, and teacher interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:46:      "expected_observation": "Independent coders should infer later manual warnings from early register statements at above-chance rates, for example calculation in Shinran, misrecognition in Dzogchen, wrong effort in gradual paths, and conceptual reification in apophatic or raft-like traditions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:55:    "Tannisho chapter 11 self power calculation Other Power text",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:56:    "Tannisho chapter 8 nembutsu not practice good act Shinran pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:57:    "Dogen Bendowa practice-realization training and enlightenment are one text",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:110:      "difference": "Dzogchen sources provide one register and its risks. The candidate compares that register with Other Power, practice-realization, divine restoration, and effortful paths without reducing them to one agency model.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:113:      "source": "Dzogchen pointing-out practitioner sources, example Tergar on pointing out true nature, https://learning.tergar.org/course_library/mingyur-rinpoches-monthly-teachings/mt-august-2019-pointing-out-your-true-nature/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:118:    "Replace the single term interface with coded values such as boundary, no-boundary, collapsed-boundary, teacher-mediated, vow-mediated, practice-realization, self-disclosure, and analyst-frame-refused.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:120:    "Test primary texts before broad tradition labels: Tannisho chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, and 11; Shinran letters; Bendowa or Genjokoan; one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual; one Christian grace or apophatic source; and one Sufi fana or baqa source.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:123:    "Read Freiberger, Clooney, Hedges, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Pargament, Shinran scholarship, Dogen practice-realization scholarship, upaya literature, and apophatic theology before raising novelty above extended."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:125:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.68 to about 0.56. The register-first discipline is strongly anticipated by comparative theology, hermeneutics, contextualist mysticism scholarship, Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model, Sharf's critique of generic experience, Pargament's agency styles, Shinran's Other Power, Dogen's practice-realization, and MN 22's self-limiting doctrine use. The remaining contribution is a useful operational extension with predictive fields, not a discovery.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:128:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners and scholars say this is standard comparative theology, upaya, self-power versus Other Power, practice-realization, apophatic self-limitation, cultural-linguistic theology, or religious coping theory. They also say the rubric does not change teaching decisions or predict student failure modes.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:137:      "Jodo Shinshu ministers and Shinran scholars",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:138:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen's practice-realization",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:139:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:147:      "Shinran, Tannisho, especially chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, and 11, trans. Taitetsu Unno, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:148:      "Dogen, Bendowa, especially sections 3, 4, 7, and 10, https://www.abuddhistlibrary.com/Buddhism/C%20-%20Zen/Ancestors/Dogen/Bendowa/Bendowa.htm"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:150:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The model may turn ordinary comparative-theology caution into a new technical vocabulary. It may also smuggle in a practitioner-event boundary, even with a self-limitation marker, in traditions where the primary grammar is no-boundary, practice-realization, divine initiative, or nondual enactment.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:151:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The closest scholarly prior art includes Oliver Freiberger on comparison as selection, description, juxtaposition, redescription, rectification, and theory formation; Paul Hedges on comparative theology and hermeneutics; Francis Clooney's comparative theology; Katz and Sharf on contextualist and anti-experience-flattening method; Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model; and Pargament's religious problem-solving styles. The audit did not fully close-read Clooney, Lindbeck, Dzogchen root texts, Meister Eckhart, Qushayri, Ibn Arabi, or Shinran's letters. That gap prevents any candidate-discovery claim.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:152:    "structural_observation": "The Tannisho strongly supports the register-first move. Its decisive register is Other Power, and it names boundary failures such as self-power, calculation, doubt, wrong teacher ownership, and confusing nembutsu with the practitioner's own good act. Bendowa is the anomaly case. It names wrong understanding, false teachers, verbal clinging, and inadequate practice, but its register is practice-realization, where training and enlightenment are not two. The proposed model reads Shinran well, but its interface language strains Dogen because an interface can imply the very separation between practitioner, practice, and realization that Bendowa rejects."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:161:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Freiberger, Clooney, Hedges, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Pargament, Shinran, Dogen, and MN 22, this idea claims that comparative work should use a specific two-layer rubric: preserve the transformation register first, then code only tradition-named vulnerabilities, safeguards, and warnings against the rubric itself. Its contribution is operational and predictive, not the discovery that traditions have different registers."
observations/codex/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate.md:20:- Challenger revision pressure: non-instrumental traditions such as Dogen practice-realization and Shinran no-calculation require a scope gate before result custody language is applied.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate.md:61:- Add source coding for whether return language is native, permitted, or imported in Dogen, Shinran, MN 22, Heart Sutra, Rinzai, and comparable Christian or Sufi materials.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Koan and huatou practice, plus Shinran's own reply to Senshin, show that a question may be deliberately used, answered, or transformed rather than simply permitted or refused.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "A question that looks wrong from outside can be the authorized method inside a lineage. Also, Shinran refuses self-calculation while still answering doctrinal questions about cause, assurance, and entrusting. This strains any simple permitted versus refused coding."
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:29:      "test_surface": "A/B inter-rater coding on SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Shinran letters, Tannisho, Bendowa, Huangbo, Dzogchen direct introduction, and Rinzai koan materials.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:33:      "expected_observation": "Dual-trained practitioners report that carrying a crossing or proof question into no-distance or Other Power settings increases self-grading, private certainty, defensiveness, or withdrawal, while carrying a repair question into ethical-return contexts increases responsibility and reachability.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:104:    "Add koan practice, Shinran doctrinal Q&A, and valid solitude as anomaly cases before public use.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:124:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:134:      "SN 22.59, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html, read against Shinran's reply to Senshin, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:135:      "Dogen Bendowa excerpts and Soto shusho itto, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf, read against Huangbo, https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:138:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Read Collingwood, Gadamer, Austin, Searle, Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, Katz, Pargament, spiritual bypassing research, VCE, Cheetah House, Pure Land studies on hakarai and Other Power, Dogen scholarship on practice-realization, and koan curriculum scholarship by Hori or Rinzai specialists before raising novelty.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:139:    "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 permits a disciplined question sequence: is this aggregate controllable, permanent, easeful, fit to regard as mine, self, or what I am? Shinran answers a doctrinal question by refusing calculation on the practicer and relocating assurance to Other Power. Dogen blocks separation of cultivation and realization, while still warning against clever slogans and requiring practice. Huangbo explicitly challenges the question What is the Way and how must it be followed? The candidate's strongest form is not that questions are bad, but that each source licenses a different question grammar with different failure modes."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:44:    "Advaita witness consciousness direct recognition not inference",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:83:    "Separate direct recognition, inference, scriptural assertion, and pragmatic refusal in the rubric.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:90:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "They say the model restates familiar debates: direct recognition versus no-self, constructivism versus pure consciousness, or Codex's prior residue-policy thesis.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:112:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The claim that both traditions share phenomenology but differ in inference may be too clean. Training may shape phenomenology itself, and Advaita often treats witness-consciousness as direct recognition rather than inference.",
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:22:- Primary-text comparison: MN 22 validates the Dhamma as a crossing tool and then warns against carrying it; the Heart Sutra denies attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita; the Mandukya Upanishad uses waking, dreaming, and deep sleep to confirm turiya; Tannisho strains self-authorizing method models by grounding release in Other Power.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:25:- Hybrid anomaly pressure: Dogen practice-realization, Rinzai post-kensho curriculum, Heart Sutra practice after no attainment, and Shinran's Other Power.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:31:The model may still overfit traditions that treat practice as a tool. Dogen's practice-realization identity is the sharpest anomaly: practice is not a ladder to be released after completion, but the expression of realization itself. Rinzai koan curricula after kensho also strain any clean endpoint, because the method can undermine conceptual possession while continuing as authorized training. Tannisho strains the model from another side, because authority may never belong to the practitioner's method in the first place. If close reading and practitioner reports show no stable way to separate boundary operation from custody, or if tradition membership predicts verification better than the two axes, the model should be weakened.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:83:Survived critique from MN 22's validated-then-abandoned raft, Heart Sutra's no-attainment-with-practice hybrid, prior-art pressure from Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein as therapeutic method, and the Dogen and Tannisho anomalies. The claim was narrowed from a broad method-completion typology into a two-axis custody model.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:155:- Prediction: A close prior argument will likely exist for self-canceling methods, but not for the specific two-axis custody test across confirming, undermining, retained, abandoned, embodied, and Other Power cases.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:158:- Next action: Search scholarship on upaya, spiritual direction, teacher authority, post-kensho training, practice-realization, Pure Land entrusting, and discursive tradition for close versions of the custody claim.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:166:- Result: Pending. MN 22 and the Heart Sutra already suggest boundary pressure, while Dogen and Tannisho may violate simple release models.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:193:- Close-read MN 22, the Heart Sutra, Mandukya Upanishad, Dogen's Genjokoan, Rinzai post-kensho training accounts, and Tannisho for explicit signs of what may guide the practitioner after insight.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If a vipassana-trained practitioner can move into Advaita self-inquiry, devotional surrender, or Dzogchen recognition without attention persistently tracking impermanence, non-ownership, or analytic deconstruction, then grain may be a comparative description rather than a lived capacity structure. Chan, Zen, modern cross-training, and eclectic contemplative therapy are especially important anomaly classes."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:11:    "The same named capacity, such as attention or self-observation, functions differently in Theravada, Advaita, Sufism, Pure Land, Dzogchen, and Soto Zen.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:35:      "expected_observation": "Vivekachudamani-style qualifications should define readiness in terms of the real versus unreal and longing for liberation. Satipatthana and later insight manuals should define readiness through impermanence, suffering, non-ownership, and ethical abandonment. Sufi manuals should orient self-knowledge toward creaturely dependence before God. Dzogchen manuals should orient preparation toward devotion, introduction, recognition, and non-distraction.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:97:      "overlap": "Internal same-run neighbor. Both ideas use the five capacity variables and compare effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:106:    "Run a small practitioner test with at least one teacher each from Theravada, Advaita, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Sufism, and Pure Land, asking whether grain changes practice sequencing."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:123:      "Dzogchen and Mahamudra teachers",
observations/codex/2026-05-26-layered-authorization-of-beginning.md:54:- Test paired traditions with shared context and different entry grammars: Zen and Jodo Shinshu, Calvinist and Wesleyan Christianity, Dzogchen and gradual-path Gelug.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:28:- Huangbo, Transmission of Mind, sections on using mind to seek mind and nothing to obtain, https://wayofsuddenawakening.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Huang-Po-The-Transmission-of-Mind.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:29:- Dogen Bendowa and shusho itto, Soto Zen explanation with Bendowa quotation, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:31:Structural observation: The close read supports a broader architecture variable, but not credit distribution alone. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 asserts an inner seer and knower through a cosmological inner-ruler grammar; it does not show a reported pressure after practice. SN 22.59 applies an ownership and control test to all aggregates and ends in disenchantment, dispassion, release, and knowledge of release; it does not leave a witness as the text's authorized remainder. Huangbo strains the sequence because it rejects using mind to seek Mind and treats objectified seeking itself as the mistake. Dogen strains it differently: practice and realization are one, so the cause-result and claimant sequence is collapsed rather than managed downstream. These sources suggest that method-reflexivity, search grammar, and practice-realization may be as upstream as credit distribution.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:47:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:67:Candidate: Huangbo search-refusal, Dogen practice-realization, and Dzogchen direct recognition cases where the tradition rejects the search sequence rather than producing a downstream remainder to manage.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:69:Why it strains the model: These cases do not cleanly fit a two-stage order of upstream credit distribution followed by downstream pressure. Huangbo says the search for Mind by mind is the problem, Dogen collapses practice and realization, and Dzogchen-style recognition can treat effortful attainment as an obscuration. If these cases are central rather than marginal, the upstream variable is not credit distribution but search grammar or reflexivity policy.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:75:- If: Credit distribution is partially coupled with remainder phenomenology. Then: Blind-coded manuals with practitioner-centered or self-inquiry architecture should show higher rates of unprompted residue markers in separate practitioner interviews, while source-centered, activity-centered, practice-realization, and search-refusal architectures should show lower or differently textured residue markers. Significant within-type variance should remain. Weakens if: Credit type perfectly predicts residue, making remainder pressure redundant; or credit type has no predictive value once practice technique, teacher, retreat intensity, doctrine, and clinical history are controlled. Test surface: Pre-registered split-source study of at least twelve practice lineages, with manual coding separated from micro-phenomenological interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:87:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with pointing-out instruction
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:88:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:89:- Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with Other Power and shinjin
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:127:- Add mandatory anomaly values: search-refusal, practice-realization, direct-recognition bypass, radical Other Power, inherited practice, cessation or nirodha, no-residue report, psychiatric vulnerability, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:27:- Shinran and Rennyo, Tannisho and Ofumi, BDK English Tripitaka, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:31:Structural observation: Orange is the strongest prescriptive incapacity case: faith's beginning, desire, assent, prayer, and right choice are assigned to grace rather than unaided natural power. Tannisho and Ofumi give a vow-held analogue: entrusting is given by Amida's working, nenbutsu after settled faith is gratitude rather than self-powered production, and the warning profile targets calculation and self-power. Benedict gives institutional and apprenticeship custody: the novice is delayed, tested, placed under a senior, repeatedly exposed to the Rule, and only then incorporated. SN 55.5 is a partial anomaly: it names association with people of integrity, hearing true Dhamma, appropriate attention, and practice in accordance with Dhamma. That is distributed support, but not necessarily a doctrine forbidding self-generated beginning. The close-read result is that the candidate's structure exists in several sources, but its categories are analyst abstractions over older grace, vow, rule, apprenticeship, and stream-entry grammars.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:33:Secondary literature gap: Search and close-reading covered accessible primary texts, local prior Lumenary records, conversion theory, legitimate peripheral participation, doctrine-as-grammar, catechumenate sources, religious coping, ritual learning, and contemplative adverse-experience methodology. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's The Nature of Doctrine, Talal Asad in full, Van Gennep and Turner in full, Japanese Pure Land scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Tibetan pointing-out manuals, Islamic bayah and Sufi tarbiya sources, Sanskrit guru-disciple materials, original-language sources, or practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:35:Risk of overread: Very high. Custody is a modern analyst term that can flatten grace, vow, obedience, refuge, rule, catechesis, initiation, community socialization, and practice-realization into one psychological metaphor. The model also risks circularity if the same passage is used to infer custody grammar and then to confirm predicted warnings or repairs.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:46:- Tannisho Other Power self-power entrusting Primal Vow
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:53:- Local prior Lumenary audit, reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md: overlap: Very close. That audit already codes entry grammar, predicts safeguards and beginner warnings, requires split-source testing, and compares grace, vow, stream-entry, and practice-realization under translation strain.; difference: The current candidate drops translation-strain scoring and adds the language of custody as the beginning's support holder.; novelty impact: Very high reduction. The operational testing burden is inherited almost unchanged.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:56:- Helena Kupari and Terhi Utriainen, Newcomers Learning Religious Ritual: Legitimate Peripheral Participation in an Orthodox Worshipping Community, https://doi.org/10.30664/ar.136236: overlap: Close empirical near-neighbor. It studies religious newcomers learning embodied Orthodox ritual through real services, old-timer dynamics, and legitimate peripheral participation.; difference: It studies micro-sociological ritual learning, not custody assignment across grace, vow, rule, teacher, ritual, and practice-realization grammars.; novelty impact: High reduction for the social-induction side. It pressures the candidate to prove that doctrine adds prediction beyond embodied participation and community learning.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:60:- Shinran and Rennyo, Tannisho and Ofumi, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf: overlap: Near exact for vow-held beginning, Other Power, blocked self-credit, critique of calculation, and gratitude rather than self-powered production after entrusting.; difference: Pure Land texts are primary cases, not a general theory of prescriptive versus retrospective custody.; novelty impact: Very high reduction for vow-held and anti-self-power examples.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:66:Unlike prior Lumenary entry ledgers, Rambo conversion theory, legitimate peripheral participation, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament's agency styles, Orange, Shinran, Benedict, and OCIA, this candidate's only distinct claim is that beginnings should be coded as custody of unstable attention, trust, agency, and interpretation, and that entry doctrine should be classified as either retrospective narration or prescriptive control. That difference is useful but thin, because prior Lumenary records and older sources already contain most of the structure.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:70:Candidate: No-threshold practice-realization, inherited religion, and successful dual-practice cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:72:Why it strains the model: The candidate assumes a distinguishable beginning where some holder takes custody before the practitioner can authorize the path. Dogen-style practice-realization weakens the before-after sequence because practice and realization are not two separate states. Inherited religion can make beginning indistinguishable from ordinary socialization. Successful dual practice can show multiple support systems coexisting without a single contested custody arrangement.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:74:Confidence effect: This lowers confidence in the model as a general theory. It can survive only as a coding heuristic with mandatory values for no-threshold, inherited-practice, practice-realization, simultaneous-custody, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:78:- If: Prescriptive custody grammar has incremental predictive force after social, institutional, and conversion-process controls. Then: Coders using only entry or doctrinal texts should predict held-out beginner warnings, verification rules, and repair instructions better when custody holder and prescriptive versus retrospective function are added to Rambo-style and Lave-Wenger-style variables. Weakens if: The added fields do not improve prediction, or all signal is absorbed by institution, teacher authority, socialization, ritual process, clinical risk, or tradition identity. Test surface: Split-source blind coding across Orange, Tannisho or Ofumi, Benedictine novitiate texts, OCIA, SN 55.5 and related Theravada manuals, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra entry source, and one Sufi or Islamic initiation source.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:92:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with practice-realization
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:93:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:104:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners and scholars say the frame is ordinary grace theology, Other Power, catechumenate, monastic formation, refuge, initiation, lineage pedagogy, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, conversion studies, or legitimate peripheral participation. They cannot identify repairs predicted by custody grammar beyond institution, teacher experience, community ecology, temperament, or clinical risk.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:124:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.76 to about 0.43. The candidate is generative, but most of its structure is already present in local Lumenary records, especially Entry-State Ledger, Threshold Grammar Under Translation Strain, Compound Entry Grammar, Layered Authorization of Beginning, and Operational Remainder Ecology. External near-neighbors further reduce the claim: Rambo covers conversion process, Lave and Wenger cover pre-mastery participation, Kupari and Utriainen apply that to religious newcomers, Lindbeck covers doctrine as grammar, Pargament covers agency distribution, Orange and Shinran give near-exact prescriptive beginning cases, Benedict and OCIA give institutional formation cases. The remaining contribution is a sharper label for prescriptive versus retrospective custody, not a discovery-level idea.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:132:- Add mandatory values for inherited practice, no-threshold, practice-realization, gradual socialization, ritual-held custody, community-held custody, teacher-held custody, vow-held custody, grace-held custody, rule-held custody, text-held custody, self-authorized entry, simultaneous custody, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:133:- Run matched comparisons where social ecology can be partially controlled, especially Jodo Shinshu versus Jodo Shu, Augustinian grace traditions versus synergist neighbors, Benedictine novitiate versus less formal lay formation, OCIA versus inherited Catholic formation, and Dzogchen pointing-out versus gradual Tibetan path training.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:135:- Treat Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, successful dual practice, and traditions that reject agency accounting as anomaly classes rather than confirming examples.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-borrowed-words-need-shared-life.md:21:- Practitioner-method source: Dogen's practice-realization in Bendowa, via local prior work and Bielefeldt's Dogen's Manuals of Zen Meditation, used as a lens for testing truth through enacted practice. Critique of the lens: it can make source history look secondary even when community, lineage, and harm require source accountability.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-borrowed-words-need-shared-life.md:85:Survived critique from comparison theory, the Chandogya and SN 22.59 carrier conflict, Dogen's practice-realization pressure, social-connection grounding, and checking-risk cautions by narrowing the claim into two distinct gates.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-borrowed-words-need-shared-life.md:157:- Prediction: Close prior art should cover comparison, functional equivalence, seeker spirituality, practice-realization, and checking risk, but should not already specify the split between doctrine provenance and seeker contact.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-borrowed-words-need-shared-life.md:158:- Result: Preliminary search found strong overlap with Smith, Freiberger, Panikkar, Wuthnow, Dogen scholarship, and OCD checking literature. Novelty should stay moderate and depend on the two-gate operational distinction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:28:- Tannisho, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:31:Structural observation: SN 22.89 already separates a formal path achievement from a remaining gradient: the noble disciple has abandoned lower fetters and does not assume 'I am this,' yet residual 'I am' conceit, desire, and obsession remain until further contemplation uproots them. SN 45.8 gives a clear practitioner-agency grammar for right effort. Tannisho gives the opposite formal marker: entrusting, non-calculation, and Amida's working, while warning against claiming nembutsu as one's own practice. Cross-reading these texts supports the candidate's two-track architecture, but also shows that much of the architecture is already available in primary sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:33:Secondary literature gap: The audit found strong near-neighbors but did not fully close-read Steve Bein, Taitetsu Unno, Pargament, Lindbeck, Trungpa, VCE coding materials, Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Rennyo letters, or Tibetan manuals beyond the cited Longchen Rabjam text. It also did not check Pali, Japanese, or Tibetan terms directly.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:35:Risk of overread: High. The claimant-layer vocabulary is strongly shaped by Theravada categories and may distort Shinran, Dzogchen, Soto Zen, and traditions that reject agency accounting. The warning-cluster prediction also risks circular coding unless safeguards are coded from a separate corpus.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:41:- Tannisho Shinran entrusting mind Amida's working not self power primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:47:- Dogen Bendowa practice and realization are one primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:53:- Tannisho, Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf; Shinran Notes, https://shinranworks.com/commentaries/notes-on-once-calling-and-many-calling/: overlap: Very close for sharp boundary, Other Power source, refusal of calculation, and warnings about claiming the practice as one's own.; difference: The candidate turns Shinran's internal grammar into a cross-tradition coding instrument.; novelty impact: Large reduction for the formal-marker and reappropriation layers in Pure Land cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:55:- Longchen Rabjam, Instruction on Trekcho, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/tibetan-masters/longchen-rabjam/lama-yangtik-trekcho-instruction: overlap: Close for recognition, critique of contrived effort, and post-recognition instructions that imply formal and ongoing dimensions.; difference: Dzogchen may not accept dissolution-gradient language, since the text emphasizes seeing the nature of mind rather than gradually dissolving a self-claiming layer.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction and a strong distortion risk.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:56:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-realization, https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/: overlap: Close as an anomaly: practice and realization are inseparable, with no clean boundary in realization and no beginning in practice.; difference: The candidate can handle Dogen only if it allows no-boundary and analyst-frame-refused values.; novelty impact: Reduces universality. It forces the rubric to become a local heuristic rather than a master structure.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:58:- Steve Bein, Self Power, Other Power, and Non-dualism in Japanese Buddhism, https://philpapers.org/rec/BEISPO: overlap: Close for comparing self-power, other-power, and nondualism as agency structures in Japanese Buddhism.; difference: The candidate adds warning clusters, stage intervals, and gradient afterwork.; novelty impact: Moderate to large reduction, especially for Japanese Buddhist agency comparison.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:66:Unlike Khemaka, Shinran, Dzogchen instructions, Dogen, Pargament, Bein, Trungpa, VCE, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says the comparative unit is a two-track transfer profile and predicts that safeguards cluster where formal agency grammar changes while partial dissolution leaves layer-specific reappropriation risks.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:70:Candidate: Dogen-style practice-realization and inherited no-threshold practice cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:74:Confidence effect: Lowers confidence in universality. The model needs no-boundary, no-threshold, practice-realization, inherited-practice, and analyst-frame-refused values before public use.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:78:- If: Formal agency grammar changes predict where manuals place specific warnings and repairs. Then: Blind coders can identify agency markers from entry or stage passages, then predict warning clusters in separate manuals better than chance and better than generic humility themes. Weakens if: Warnings distribute evenly, track only intensity or teacher authority, or cannot be predicted from formal markers. Test surface: Split-corpus manual coding across Theravada, Jodo Shinshu, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Soto Zen, Christian grace, and Sufi fana or baqa sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:79:- If: Partial dissolution produces layer-specific reappropriation patterns. Then: Practitioner interviews distinguish view-release, affective conceit, habit, narrative identity, and social credential layers, and each layer predicts different forms of owning the insight. Weakens if: Reports do not separate layers, or reappropriation is fully explained by ordinary pride, teacher feedback, status incentives, trauma, or community role. Test surface: Micro-phenomenological interviews with practitioners who report partial awakening, shinjin, direct recognition, surrender, or nondual insight.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:87:- Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with shinjin and Other Power
