reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:102:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say this is standard fetter theory, Shinshu non-calculation, Dzogchen stabilization, spiritual materialism, upaya, or ordinary pastoral caution. They cannot name repairs beyond familiar warnings about pride, striving, doubt, role identity, or teacher dependence.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:122:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.61 to about 0.54. The two-track formulation is useful, but the primary-text close read shows that formal attainment versus residual self-claiming is already explicit in SN 22.89, Other Power boundary and anti-calculation repair are explicit in Shinran, and reappropriation is strongly anticipated by spiritual materialism. The remaining contribution is a comparative coding synthesis with testable warning-cluster predictions.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.md:129:- Add mandatory values for no-boundary, no-threshold, inherited-practice, practice-realization, Other Power refusal, recognition-event, continuous authorization, and undecidable.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-beginning-has-a-grammar-and-a-threshold.md:61:- Design a vignette study that codes teacher guidance across Jodo Shinshu, Theravada, Catholic spiritual direction, Dzogchen, recovery, and therapy settings.
