reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.json:119:    "Treat activity-centered and ground-centered categories as the only possible novelty zones, and search Dogen, Advaita, Dzogchen, and nondual scholarship for close prior forms.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.json:123:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.74 to about 0.48. The five-type comparative frame is generative, but the main structure is anticipated by Pargament's religious coping styles, God-control attribution research, Christian monergism and synergism, Japanese self-power and other-power, Sri Vaishnava prapatti debates, Sufi station-state distinctions, Dogen practice-realization, and local Lumenary work.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:28:- Tannisho, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf; Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/commentaries/notes-on-once-calling-and-many-calling/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:30:Structural observation: SN 22.59 negates ownership of all aggregates and moves through disenchantment, dispassion, and release, so continuity is carried by instruction, discernment, and practice process rather than an authorized self. Chandogya repeatedly authorizes an underlying Self, but 6.14 also uses a teacher and stepwise inquiry as the way a blindfolded person finds the way home. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 relocates continuity into an unseen inner controller. Tannisho relocates decisive support into Amida's vow, true entrusting, teacher lineage, and non-calculating nembutsu, while refusing ownership of disciples or practice. This close read strongly supports the candidate's comparative frame, but also shows that much of the structure is already explicit in primary texts.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The audit used accessible primary translations and open academic sources, but did not fully read Collins, Siderits, Harvey, Albahari, Mahmood's Politics of Piety, Bourdieu, Rambo, Lave and Wenger, Shinran's full Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, or Tibetan manuals beyond Longchen Rabjam. Pali, Sanskrit, Japanese, and Tibetan terms were not checked directly.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:49:- Tannisho Shinran Other Power self power calculation primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:50:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:62:- Tannisho, Dogen Bendowa, and Longchen Rabjam Trekcho primary materials, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf; https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/; https://www.lotsawahouse.org/tibetan-masters/longchen-rabjam/lama-yangtik-trekcho-instruction: overlap: Very close primary evidence for theologically relocated support, no-boundary practice-realization, guru reliance, vows, solitude, and post-recognition training.; difference: The candidate names these as variables in one cross-tradition model.; novelty impact: Large reduction. Several allegedly new variables are already visible in the source texts.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:71:Candidate: Dogen's practice-realization and inherited-practice cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:73:Why it strains the model: Dogen's Bendowa denies a clean boundary in realization and denies a beginning in practice. Inherited religious participation can also preserve continuity before any explicit self-negating doctrine is consciously adopted. In both cases, the model may impose a migration story where the tradition presents no transfer, no threshold, or no separate continuity problem.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:75:Confidence effect: This lowers confidence in any universal causal claim. The model should remain an interpretive coding heuristic unless split-source tests show predictive gain over practice-realization, socialization, and institutional history.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:79:- If: Dissolution target and residue policy exert independent pressure on continuity placement. Then: Coders who see only doctrinal negation passages can predict above baseline whether later manuals locate support in effort, attention, teacher, vow, grace, ritual, community, text, or no-boundary practice-realization. Weakens if: Prediction fails, or ritual form, institution type, teacher authority, socialization pattern, or historical borrowing predicts support placement better than dissolution target and residue policy. Test surface: Split-source blind coding across Theravada, Advaita, Soto Zen, Jodo Shinshu, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Christian grace, Sufi fana and baqa, and secular mindfulness manuals.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:81:- If: Practice ecology can precede doctrine but should leave historical traces when it does. Then: Where support structures predate doctrinal refinement, later doctrine explicitly explains, legitimates, or polices already existing teacher, ritual, vow, or institutional arrangements. Weakens if: Historical cases show no relation between prior ecology and later doctrine, or show doctrine changing without support-ecology change and without new warning or verification patterns. Test surface: Historical comparison of Shinran communities, Soto monastic practice, Theravada reform movements, modern mindfulness programs, and Christian grace controversies.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:89:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with practice-realization
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:90:- Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with shinjin, Other Power, and non-calculation
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:91:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with recognition, guru reliance, and post-recognition conduct
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:103:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say this is standard no-self continuity, Other Power, practice-realization, guru-yoga, grace, upaya, spiritual materialism, or ordinary pastoral sequencing. They cannot identify new predictions, repairs, or failure clusters.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:130:- Add mandatory anomaly values: no-boundary practice-realization, inherited practice, no-threshold, vow-held, grace-held, teacher-recognition, ritual-first, institution-first, secular extraction, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:130:      "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, Heart Sutra, Shinran On Jinen-Honi, and Dogen Bendowa or practice-realization sources, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/words-of-the-buddha/heart-sutra, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/, https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:132:    "risk_of_overread": "High. External holding can be wise guidance, ordinary sponsorship, clinical triage, coercive authority, approval dependence, or OCD reassurance. No-check can mean healthy rest, avoidance, depression drift, or Dogen-style non-instrumentality. The bypasser, scorer, and oscillator labels are too crude without validated measures and concrete behavior markers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:134:    "structural_observation": "Ignatius is the closest primary-text neighbor. The director adapts exercises to the exercitant, receives reports of movements and thoughts, reveals dangerous secrecy to a confessor or spiritual person, and is also restrained from seizing the exercitant's final choice. The scruple notes already distinguish useful sensitivity from harmful over-fineness and counsel a mean. MN 22 adds that the raft must be grasped correctly before release, so release is not a generic self-check. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while retaining reliance on Prajnaparamita. Shinran and Dogen strain the whole model because no-calculation and practice-realization refuse a clean separable product that the practitioner can audit."
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-independently-coded-function-by-placement-analysis-plus-post-gap-ad.md:18:**Steelman:** The proponent is not merely saying that no-self traditions secretly need a self. The stronger claim is architectural: any path that dissolves, denies, or transcends ordinary selfhood still has to preserve some functional capacities long enough for training to happen, such as receiving instruction, remembering, correcting error, sustaining attention, and recognizing or integrating change. Different traditions solve this pressure differently, and those solutions should predict their effort theory, verification rules, warnings, and fruit. Buddhism preserves causal process without owner, Advaita preserves deepest identity while dissolving apparent process, Dogen collapses practice and realization, and Sufi fana and baqa bridge self-loss through divine relation.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-independently-coded-function-by-placement-analysis-plus-post-gap-ad.md:24:I concede four things cleanly. First, the distributed-containment model is genuinely better at explaining other-power, devotional, and teacher-field traditions; the original model underweighted these. Second, Engler's clinical formulation covers the safety ground and has priority on the practical insight. Third, the title overstated universality; the claim is graded, not universal. Fourth, the four management strategies are heuristic mixtures, not clean types. What I defend is more specific. The distributed-containment model and the minimum-self model are not competitors. They answer different questions, and the containment model presupposes the functional one. You cannot distribute continuity until you know what must be continued. The functions are: receiving instruction or transmission, sustaining effort or openness, correcting error, and recognizing change. Where these are housed is a second-order question. The irreducible receiving surface is not trivially true. Traditions that push it thinnest, Dzogchen and radical Pure Land, develop the most precise protocols around exactly that thin point. Dzogchen requires a specific relational context, precise timing, and teacher judgment of readiness. Shinran developed elaborate doctrinal machinery to explain how even entrusting is given without self-power. If the receiving surface were trivial, these traditions would not need to engineer around it so carefully. The Engler formulation is sequential: first build ego, then dissolve. The revised minimum-self model is concurrent: a beginning vipassana practitioner needs enough self to sit and follow instructions while those instructions are already framing the self as impersonal aggregates. This is not a before-and-after problem but a during problem that the practice manages at every session. The management strategies, even as heuristics, predict architecture that the containment model alone does not. Tell me a tradition's primary continuity strategy and I can predict its map type, warning profile, and verification method. Causal continuity yields condition-tracking maps (Abhidharma). Ontological identity yields confusion-accounting theory (adhyasa). Temporal collapse resists stage sequencing (Dogen). Divine restoration concentrates teacher authority at the annihilation moment (Sufi sheikh at fana). These predictions require knowing both what continuity function is at stake and what the dissolution target is. Container strength alone cannot generate them. The human-condition revision: the model matters most for people encountering dissolution teachings outside traditional containers. When the container is strong, the practitioner's receiving surface can be thin because the ecology carries load. When the container is weak or absent (app-based meditation, books without teachers, retreat weekends without follow-up, psychedelic experiences without integration), the practitioner's own self-capacity must carry more of the continuity burden. The danger zone is the mismatch: a person with low self-capacity entering a path with weak distributed support, or a person with high self-management entering a strongly distributed path that demands a surrender they cannot give. The primary cohort is secular seekers, trauma survivors drawn to dissolution language, high-achievers approaching practice with optimization mindsets, cross-tradition samplers without sustained teacher relationships, and clinicians or chaplains who need to assess when practice helps versus harms. The non-fit case is practitioners in intact traditional communities where the distributed ecology already manages continuity; for them, the model adds nothing. Also outside scope: acute psychiatric crisis (clinical stabilization, not contemplative architecture) and single-lineage practitioners whose receiving surface and dissolution target are always aligned by design. The deepest crux is whether function-identification adds predictive power beyond placement-identification. If knowing w...
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:71:- If: Even direct-recognition traditions preserve return constraints. Then: Advaita, Dzogchen, Zen, and apophatic sources that speak strongly about immediate recognition still retain some constraint through teacher, text, lineage, vow, conduct, compassion, or ordinary functioning. Weakens if: Mature sources explicitly authorize private silence as sufficient warrant with no correction, conduct, lineage, or aftercare, and practitioners show stable integration without those constraints. Test surface: Close reading plus practitioner interviews asking for concrete misrecognition, warning, and repair cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:79:- Advaita and Dzogchen teachers who teach direct recognition
observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:15:The closest prior argument is local becoming in relativity: Stein, Arthur, Dieks, and Savitt already treat proper time, light cones, and causal diamonds as ways to avoid a single global present. The distinct move is not to claim a new physics of time. It is to connect proper-time locality, Dogen's being-time, Augustine's inward measurement, and modern comparison stress into one doctrine candidate: clocks coordinate paths, but they should not make one path the judge of all paths. Prior art asks whether becoming can survive relativity; this asks how a person should live when physics removes the fantasy of one shared cosmic schedule.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:27:- Primary contemplative comparison: Dogen, Shobogenzo Uji, refuses separation between being and time and warns against treating time as merely flying away; notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:29:- Practitioner-method source: Augustine's inward observation was used as the first lens, watching how memory, attention, and expectation make duration legible. Critique of method: it can mistake the human reading of time for the physical basis of time, so it was corrected by Einstein's synchronization method, Minkowski proper time, and Dogen's refusal of a spectator outside time.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:34:The strongest objection is that the idea may be local becoming with spiritual and therapeutic clothing. Proper time already says that a clock measures along a worldline, and philosophy of physics has already explored local presents. Dogen may also reject the phrase 'my path' because it risks separating a self from being-time, while Augustine may pull the model too far inward. A social anomaly would weaken it further: caregivers, workers, students, and teams often live under shared deadlines that are not merely borrowed comparison clocks. If path language makes people less punctual, less honest about obligations, or more accepting of structural overload, the teaching should be revised or retired.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:90:Survived close reading of Einstein's clock synchronization, Minkowski proper time, Augustine's inward measurement, Dogen's no-separation, Plotinus on eternity and succession, and prior-art pressure from local becoming in relativity.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:188:### Dogen No-Separation Pressure
observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:213:- Close-read Dogen Uji against Stein, Dieks, and Arthur. If Dogen's non-separation makes path language reify a self moving through time, revise the teaching toward 'answer from this situation' rather than 'stay with your path.'
findings/convergences/2026-05-30-two-cruxes-remain-open-first-the-human-condition-crux-does-any-self-administer.md:13:Two cruxes remain open. First, the human-condition crux: does any self-administered safety routing reduce verdict-making, or does the act of self-classifying (evidence or not, instrumental or autotelic, scrupulous or not) merely relocate the verdict onto whether one sorted and returned correctly, feeding the very self-surveillance the teaching means to relieve. Second, the originality crux: once the warrant attaches only to conduct and relationship, is this still a teaching about silence-as-evidence, or has it become the near-general rule that no inner state licenses harm to conduct and care, with the Upanishad, sutta, Dogen, and Shinran sources decorating rather than grounding it. Neither was settled in dialogue; both are routed to a blind coding test and a stratified pilot.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Radical Jodo Shinshu, especially Tannisho chapters 8 and 10, where nembutsu is not the practitioner's practice or good act and no working is true working.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If even hearing, saying, entrusting, and gratitude are Amida's working rather than trained human functions, then the analyst's transfer language may smuggle self-power into a tradition built to reject that framing. Dogen also strains the model because practice-realization collapses bridge and arrival rather than transferring ownership from one holder to another."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:12:    "Other-power, direct-introduction, effort-centered, and practice-realization paths differ by transfer point, support holder, credited source, forbidden claimant, safeguard, and repair.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:27:      "expected_observation": "Pure Land texts should warn against calculation, Dzogchen texts against contrivance and premature recognition, Soto texts against gaining idea, early Buddhist texts against appropriation of aggregates or attainment ownership, and Gita-style karma-yoga texts against fruit ownership.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:41:      "test_surface": "Inter-rater coding of matched pairs such as Soto and Dzogchen, Pure Land and Christian grace, Theravada and karma-yoga.",
