reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:116:    "Code primary manuals before broad tradition labels, beginning with SN 45.8, Tannisho chapters 1, 6, 8, and 11, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, Bendowa or Dogen practice-realization sources, and one Christian grace manual.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:121:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.53 to about 0.44. The rubric is generative, but its parts are heavily anticipated by religious coping styles, self-power and other-power discourse, Dogen, Dzogchen manuals, the raft and upaya pattern, Engler, and local Lumenary priors. Treat as a consolidation unless inter-rater coding shows new predictive value.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:134:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:145:      "Shinran, Tannisho, A Record in Lament of Divergences, https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:148:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The search found close prior structures in religious coping styles, self-power and other-power, Dogen practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Engler on ego strength before no-self, the Buddhist raft and upaya pattern, and local Lumenary capacity-ledger and credit-distribution work. I did not find the exact field list as a cross-tradition coding sheet, but the core agency-allocation and means-end reversal are well established.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:149:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 makes right effort operational and practitioner-facing: desire, endeavor, persistence, intent, and maintenance of skillful qualities are all assigned to the monk's practice field. Tannisho reverses the claimant grammar: nembutsu is not a practice or good act when it arises from Other Power, and claims such as my disciples are rejected because the working belongs to Amida. The comparison supports a real difference in claimant policy, but Tannisho is not a late handoff after training. It often refuses self-claim from the entrance, so the model needs a no-transfer or analyst-frame-refused value."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:161:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament, self-power and other-power debates, Dogen practice-realization, and local Lumenary credit models, this idea says the decisive unit is a timed transfer for each required function, with observable safeguards and repairs at that transfer point."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:16:- Traditions authorize or refuse some remainder after critique, such as self, no-self continuity, grace, vow, teacher recognition, practice-realization, ritual, community, or silence.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:27:- Tannisho, sections 1, 6, 10, and 11, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:29:- Dogen Bendowa and shusho itto, Soto Zen source, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:32:Structural observation: The primary texts support an interaction field but also reduce originality. Tannisho makes entry depend on entrusting to Amida's vow, relocates decisive efficacy to Other Power, and warns against self-power, teacher ownership, and self-will. SN 22.59 negates ownership of the five aggregates and moves through disenchantment, release, and knowledge of release, without authorizing a hidden self as remainder. Dogen strains the sequence because practice and realization are one, so beginning and fruit cannot be cleanly separated. The Gita complicates the model by mixing action, multiple causes, divine inner rulership, and final surrender, so one text may contain several entry-residue logics by chapter and voice.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:34:Secondary literature gap: This audit checked accessible primary translations, local prior Lumenary audits, and open sources on conversion, rites of passage, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, situated learning, Pure Land Other Power, Christian grace, and practice-realization. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's full book, Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Latin, or Chinese originals, Shinran scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Sufi bayah and fana sources, Dzogchen pointing-out manuals, or practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:45:- "Tannisho" Other Power self-power Primal Vow chapter 11
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:46:- "Dogen" Bendowa practice realization shusho itto
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:55:- Arnold van Gennep and Victor Turner on rites of passage and liminality, overview at https://www.britannica.com/topic/rite-of-passage: overlap: Close for threshold structure, separation, transition, reincorporation, ritual holding, danger, and change in religious or social status.; difference: Rites-of-passage theory does not focus on what remains authorized after self-critique, no-self, grace, vow, or practice-realization.; novelty impact: High reduction for threshold and beginning language, with some remaining novelty for residue interaction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:58:- Shinran and Tannisho Other Power sources, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf: overlap: Near exact for vow-held entry, blocked self-credit, warning against self-power, and transformation disclosed through entrusting.; difference: Tannisho is one tradition-internal case, not a cross-tradition predictive rubric.; novelty impact: Very high reduction for Pure Land examples and strong pressure against recoding Other Power as practitioner capacity.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:59:- Dogen practice-realization and shusho itto, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf: overlap: Very close anomaly. Practice and realization are one, beginner practice is already implicated in realization, and instrumental entry-to-fruit sequencing is rejected.; difference: The candidate can include this as no-threshold or practice-realization, but Dogen is not easily treated as entry plus later residue.; novelty impact: High anomaly pressure. The model needs analyst-frame-refused and no-break values.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:66:Unlike Rambo, Van Gennep, Turner, Lindbeck, Pargament, Lave and Wenger, VCE, Shinran, Dogen, Orange, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says the key test is additive prediction: independently coded residue authorization and entry grammar should interact to predict held-out safeguards, warnings, effort theories, verification rules, and repairs better than entry-only, residue-only, agency-style, social-ecology, tradition-identity, or source-layer baselines.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:70:Candidate: Dogen practice-realization and inherited religious participation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:72:Why it strains the model: Dogen-style practice-realization collapses the ordinary sequence of beginning, method, and fruit. Inherited participation may have no salient first-break event. Both cases strain a model that assumes transformation begins through a narratable threshold and later authorizes a remainder.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:74:Confidence effect: Lowers confidence unless the rubric includes no-threshold, no-break, inherited-practice, practice-realization, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable values, and still makes held-out predictions.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:79:- If: Traditions with similar entry forms but different residue policies should develop different verification and repair rules. Then: Teacher-encounter traditions that authorize hidden Self, no-self release, direct recognition, or grace should verify and repair different failures even when the visible entry event looks similar. Weakens if: Similar teacher-encounter forms produce the same warning and repair profile regardless of residue authorization. Test surface: Paired comparison of Advaita self-inquiry, Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out, Zen encounter, and Christian spiritual direction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:80:- If: Traditions with similar residue authorization but different entry grammar should produce different beginner safeguards. Then: Two traditions that both authorize non-acquired reality should differ if one begins through vow or grace, another through direct recognition, and another through continuous practice-realization. Weakens if: Safeguards track only residue authorization or only social institution, not entry grammar. Test surface: Within-family and cross-family comparisons: Pure Land, Christian grace, Soto Zen, Dzogchen, and Advaita.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:81:- If: Circularity severity should predict auxiliary support structures. Then: High-circularity paths should rely more on vow, grace, teacher authorization, ritual threshold, paradox pedagogy, community holding, or no-threshold practice-realization. Weakens if: Circularity severity does not correlate with auxiliary supports once social ecology and institutional inheritance are controlled. Test surface: Pre-registered coding across at least eight traditions, with inter-rater reliability.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:91:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:105:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say the framework is obvious as self-power versus Other Power, grace versus works, upaya, conversion stages, or doctrine-as-grammar, and it would not alter sequencing, warning, verification, or repair. They cannot identify cases where the interaction predicts more than teacher experience, tradition identity, social context, or clinical risk.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:125:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.53. The synthesis is useful and testable, but most components have strong near-neighbors: conversion theory for entry process, rites-of-passage theory for thresholds, Lindbeck for grammar, Pargament for agency distribution, Shinran and Orange for vow or grace-held beginnings, Dogen for practice-realization collapse, VCE for factor-separated contemplative outcomes, and prior Lumenary audits for residue, first-break, entry-state, threshold grammar, claimability, support, and operational remainder ecology. The remaining contribution is a split-source interaction test with additive predictive burden.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:133:- Add mandatory values for no-threshold, no-break, inherited practice, gradual socialization, vow-held entry, grace-held entry, teacher-recognition, practice-realization, radical Other Power, ritual-first entry, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:25:- Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, Blofeld translation hosted at https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a1-chun-chou-record.htm and https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm, read with Dogen Bendowa excerpts at https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and Soto shusho itto note at https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:27:Structural observation: SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 explicitly authorize seeing, observing, examining, disenchantment, release, and the knowledge that the task is done. That is a staged investigative grammar. Huangbo repeatedly treats seeking Mind with mind, forming concepts of the Way, or making the Way into a road as the very distortion. Dogen's practice-realization unity blocks a simple cause-then-result reading, while Soto material also says Dogen emphasized active practice because realization is already present. The candidate's gate is textually plausible, but only if it codes the native practice grammar rather than broad tradition names.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:29:Secondary literature gap: Search further in Collingwood on the logic of question and answer, Gadamer on the priority of the question, Asad on discursive tradition, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Austin on felicity conditions, Sharf and Katz on contextualism, Dogen scholarship on shusho itto, Chan studies on Huangbo and Bankei, Dzogchen direct-introduction literature, VCE and Cheetah House safety literature, and spiritual bypassing research.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:31:Risk of overread: High. The model can make search-refusal too clean. Huangbo taught through dialogue, Dogen built a practice institution, and Dzogchen no-path language often requires teacher transmission. The modern cohort is clear but narrow: stable over-managers and perfectionistic practitioners who audit their inner state. It is not for beginners needing inquiry, people using non-inquiry to avoid repair, OCD or scrupulosity, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, acute trauma, addiction withdrawal, or medical blackout concerns.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:37:- Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking using mind to seek Mind
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:38:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto practice verification
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:39:- Dzogchen no path no practice direct introduction teacher support
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:45:- Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a1-chun-chou-record.htm and https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm: overlap: Huangbo already says seeking, conceptual road-making, and using mind to seek Mind are errors.; difference: The candidate turns Huangbo's instruction into a comparative coding gate for residue analysis and a modern practice-safety rule.; novelty impact: Strong downgrade for the core insight that the search itself can be the problem.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:46:- Dogen Bendowa and Soto shusho itto, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf: overlap: Practice and realization are treated as inseparable, which already blocks a simple before-and-after result model.; difference: The candidate groups Dogen with search-refusal paths, but Dogen still insists on active, continuous practice.; novelty impact: Moderate downgrade and anomaly pressure. Dogen supports the gate but resists any no-practice simplification.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:53:Unlike Huangbo, Dogen, Collingwood, Gadamer, VCE, and prior Lumenary no-management records, this idea's specific contribution is a precondition test before remainder coding: only ask what remains if the path first authorizes a self-negation event with an after.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:57:Candidate: Rinzai koan and huatou practice deliberately uses an impossible or destabilizing question to create great doubt, while Dzogchen can deny path and result yet still require direct introduction, teacher relation, and integration.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:61:Confidence effect: Lowers confidence in a binary search-sequence versus search-refusal model. Raises confidence only for a more cautious codebook that includes search-refusal, question-as-medicine, no-distance-with-support, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:65:- If: The precondition gate has independent coding value. Then: Blind coders using only doctrinal or instruction passages can sort cases into search-sequence, search-refusal, question-as-medicine, no-distance-with-support, and undecidable above chance before seeing warnings or repairs. Weakens if: Coders cannot agree, or their labels are just tradition labels, teacher style, or genre labels in disguise. Test surface: Inter-rater coding on SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Huangbo, Bendowa, Tannisho, one Dzogchen direct-introduction source, and one Rinzai koan source.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:66:- If: Remainder pressure is not universal. Then: In search-sequence cases, warnings and repairs cluster around misidentification, clinging, effort, and post-release integration. In search-refusal cases, warnings cluster around seeking, monitoring, conceptualization, and self-grading. Weakens if: Warnings and failures in search-refusal cases are predicted just as well by support-holder loss, teacher absence, trauma, sleep loss, or institutional harm without using the precondition gate. Test surface: Split-source coding, code path grammar from one corpus and predict held-out warnings, repairs, and practitioner failure cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:73:- Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:74:- Chan or Zen teachers familiar with Huangbo and Bankei
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:76:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:77:- Jodo Shinshu teachers for Other Power contrast
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:88:Answers that reduce originality: Originality falls if practitioners say this is standard pedagogy under no-seeking, shusho itto, Other Power, direct introduction, koan great doubt, or ordinary spiritual-bypassing triage, and if the gate adds no decisions beyond existing teacher judgment.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:108:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.46 to 0.36. The core no-seeking and no-result logic is old in Huangbo, Dogen, Dzogchen, Shinran-adjacent no-calculation sources, and prior Lumenary no-management records. Retain as an extended precondition-gate hypothesis only if split-source coding shows predictive gain.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:113:- Build a precondition codebook with values for search-sequence, search-refusal, no-distance-with-support, question-as-medicine, received-without-calculation, practice-realization, valid-solitude, unsafe-avoidance, clinical-routing, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:115:- Add Rinzai koan practice and Dzogchen direct introduction as anomaly classes, not supporting examples.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-a-tradition-s-dissolution-target-independently-predict-where-contin.md:24:I concede more than I expected. The challenger is right that 'minimum self' over-internalizes the operative continuity, that residue policy is a genuine variable my model lacked, and that other-power traditions expose a real weakness in my original framing. These are not minor adjustments. But the core insight survives in revised form. Even Shinran's practitioner, who contributes nothing but shinjin, must be the kind of being that can receive shinjin. Receptivity is thinner than agency, but it is irreducibly internal. A rock in the temple does not receive the nembutsu. A dog hearing the chanting does not entrust. Whatever shinjin is, it requires a being structured to be addressed by it. More importantly, the challenger's model treats distribution and residue as independent variables, but I think distribution is downstream of what the teaching dissolves. Jodo Shinshu externalizes continuity to Amida's vow precisely because its teaching negates self-powered agency. Advaita internalizes continuity to Atman precisely because its teaching negates the empirical person while preserving ultimate identity. Dogen compresses continuity into the present precisely because his teaching negates the temporal gap between practice and realization. If these correspondences hold across traditions, the dissolution target is the generative pressure that determines where continuity must migrate. The challenger's model is richer than mine in vocabulary but poorer in causal structure. So I revise: the operative concept is not minimum self but minimum receptivity, which is the irreducible internal capacity to be addressed and transformed. Beyond that floor, each tradition requires additional capacities in proportion to how much of the work it assigns to the practitioner rather than to external supports. The distribution of continuity is constrained by the scope of negation. The residue policy is a genuine third variable that completes the model. The crux is whether distribution follows from dissolution or floats free. That is an empirical question about the actual architecture of contemplative paths, and the paired-tradition test I describe would settle it.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-a-tradition-s-dissolution-target-independently-predict-where-contin.md:30:The revision is transformed, and in several respects improved. It no longer forces all traditions into a self-powered contemplative frame, and it rightly treats Shinran, grace, vow, teacher, and community as serious carriers of continuity. I would not call it simply stronger, because the original claim's central noun has been surrendered. A minimum self has become minimum receptivity plus distributed continuity plus residue policy. That is a different model, not just a repaired version of the old one. The strongest surviving insight is that negation creates architectural pressure. If a path negates self-powered agency, it will likely move continuity toward vow, grace, teacher, or communal form. If it negates the empirical person while preserving ultimate identity, it will likely locate continuity in a deeper ontological layer. That is a good causal hypothesis. But it still has to compete with a historical one: traditions may first develop concrete practices, institutions, devotional habits, and authority structures, then formulate doctrines that rationalize where continuity already sits. So the named crux is nearly right, but should be sharpened. The question is not only whether distribution follows from dissolution or varies independently. The question is whether dissolution target predicts distribution after rival explanations are controlled. If it does, the proponent's transformed model becomes genuinely strong. If it does not, minimum receptivity remains a true but thin floor, and the better explanatory unit is the full continuity ecology of a path.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.json:144:      "MN 22 raft simile, Heart Sutra no attainment, and Dogen practice-realization, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/words-of-the-buddha/heart-sutra, https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.json:146:    "risk_of_overread": "High. Spiritual release texts can be misused to justify quitting hard work, while Dogen can be misused to justify endless practice with no deliverable. The engine evidence is procedural, not doctrinal: it repeatedly ignored a logged audit or merge step.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.json:148:    "structural_observation": "Zhuangzi and MN 22 both support release of a tool after its work is done, but they presuppose a real catch or crossing. MN 22 also stresses proper grasp before release, which prevents premature quitting. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita, so no-attainment is not simple inactivity. Dogen strains the model most, because practice and realization are inseparable, which blocks a universal before-and-after completion rule. These primary texts support a scoped after-use discipline, not the broad claim that finishing is always the next virtue."
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-careful-tradi.md:9:Both agents converge that the original capacity-ledger formulation was too strong, that ontological register must come before capacity or interface analysis, and that Other Power and nondual traditions cannot be faithfully described as if decisive transformation were simply a practitioner-owned capacity.
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-careful-tradi.md:13:Does the revised two-layer model produce comparative insight beyond careful tradition-specific reading, and can it map interface risks without reproducing the calculating or dualistic stance that traditions such as Shinran's Other Power, Dzogchen, and practice-realization warn against?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "No-threshold entry: inherited practice and Dogen's practice-realization grammar, especially Bendowa's claim that beginner practice is already original realization and that there is no beginning in practice.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If a path is entered by gradual socialization, inherited belonging, or a practice-realization grammar that refuses a boundary between practice and realization, then no discrete entry-state capacity may be identifiable. The ledger may become a total life-history description rather than a threshold model. It also becomes hard to distinguish grammar from institution, family, habit, and ordinary enculturation."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:28:      "expected_observation": "In paired communities with similar diaspora context, demographics, institutional density, and teacher access, Other Power or grace grammars will produce more warnings against self-powered calculation, more trust and receiving language, and different repair instructions than effort-centered traditions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:42:      "test_surface": "Augustinian versus Pelagian disputes, jiriki versus tariki debates, gradual versus sudden Chan, or Soto practice-realization versus koan-curriculum entry.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:59:    "Tannisho Shinran Other Power self power nembutsu not practice good act chapter 8 translation",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:62:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization beginner practice realization translation",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:98:      "difference": "Shinran gives one path grammar, not a cross-tradition predictive rubric.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:99:      "novelty_impact": "High reduction and high anomaly pressure. The model must avoid recoding Other Power as an analyst-owned capacity.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:100:      "overlap": "Very close for forbidden self-claiming and load relocation. Shinran explicitly treats Other Power as decisive and denies that nembutsu is self-power practice.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:101:      "source": "Shinran, Chapter on Practice, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/the-major-expositions/chapter-on-practice/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:131:    "Add rubric values for no-threshold, inherited practice, gradual socialization, recommitment threshold, crisis threshold, teacher-recognition threshold, vow-held threshold, grace-held threshold, practice-realization, and analyst-frame-refused.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:134:    "Use inherited-practice and Dogen-style no-beginning cases as anomaly tests rather than marginal examples.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:138:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.64. The distributed-entry and threshold pieces are strongly anticipated by Rambo's conversion model, liminality, situated learning, religious socialization, upaya, Pargament's agency styles, Engler's prerequisites, Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic grammar, and Shinran's Other Power. The remaining contribution is a promising operational synthesis: a split-source predictive rubric linking entry capacity loci to tradition-specific warning and repair patterns.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:147:      "Does calling entrusting, grace, recognition, inherited belonging, or practice-realization a capacity distort your tradition's own language?",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:151:      "Jodo Shinshu ministers and Shinran scholars",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:155:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with pointing-out",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:164:      "Shinran, Chapter on Practice, Collected Works of Shinran, plus Tannisho, Matheson Trust page, https://shinranworks.com/the-major-expositions/chapter-on-practice/ and https://www.themathesontrust.org/library/tannisho-shin-buddhist-aphorisms"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:167:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit searched conversion theory, religious coping, legitimate peripheral participation, liminality, upaya, transformative learning, religious socialization, Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model, Shinran, SN 45.8, Dogen, Augustine, and the Council of Orange. It did not sufficiently close-read Kyogyoshinsho beyond the Chapter on Practice, Augustine and Pelagius in full primary-text sequence, Longchenpa or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals, Sufi bayah and fana texts, or original-language terms for entrusting, effort, vow, grace, and capacity. That gap blocks a candidate-discovery claim.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:168:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 makes the path legible through cultivated factors: right view, right resolve, right effort, right mindfulness, and right concentration are named as functions a practitioner develops. Shinran's Chapter on Practice reverses the ownership grammar: nembutsu is not self-power practice, Other Power is the decisive cause, and the Name or Primal Vow carries the decisive function. This supports the ledger's contrast because similar threshold functions are allocated to different loci. It also threatens the model because Pure Land sources may reject the analyst's capacity language rather than merely move capacity from practitioner to vow."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:177:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike conversion-process theory, religious coping theory, upaya pedagogy, situated learning, liminality theory, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar model, Engler's capacity prerequisites, and Shinran's Other Power grammar, this idea claims that path entry can be coded as a pre-practice distributed ledger plus a normative beginning grammar, and that this pairing should predict later safeguards, warnings, verification practices, and failure modes better than either entry ecology or doctrine alone."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.md:17:- The same named capacity, such as attention or self-observation, functions differently in Theravada, Advaita, Sufism, Pure Land, Dzogchen, and Soto Zen.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.md:52:- The Capacity Ledger of Gift and Effort, observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort.md: overlap: Internal same-run neighbor. Both ideas use the five capacity variables and compare effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization.; difference: Capacity Ledger scores load placement. Grain adds directionality within each load and predicts resistance when a trained direction is repurposed.; novelty impact: Moderate to high internal reduction. Grain may be the more specific synthesis, but it depends on the same architecture.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.md:62:Why it strains the model: If a vipassana-trained practitioner can move into Advaita self-inquiry, devotional surrender, or Dzogchen recognition without attention persistently tracking impermanence, non-ownership, or analytic deconstruction, then grain may be a comparative description rather than a lived capacity structure. Chan, Zen, modern cross-training, and eclectic contemplative therapy are especially important anomaly classes.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.md:69:- If: Primary manuals should grain prerequisites toward their final dissolution. Then: Vivekachudamani-style qualifications should define readiness in terms of the real versus unreal and longing for liberation. Satipatthana and later insight manuals should define readiness through impermanence, suffering, non-ownership, and ethical abandonment. Sufi manuals should orient self-knowledge toward creaturely dependence before God. Dzogchen manuals should orient preparation toward devotion, introduction, recognition, and non-distraction. Weakens if: Prerequisites are generic across manuals, such as calm, attention, ethics, and perseverance, with little relation to the final insight language of each path. Test surface: Blind coding of Visuddhimagga chapter 1, Vivekachudamani vv. 17-30, Cloud of Unknowing chapters 3-6, al-Qushayri's Risala, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, and Satipatthana-related materials.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.md:79:- Dzogchen and Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.md:117:- Run a small practitioner test with at least one teacher each from Theravada, Advaita, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Sufism, and Pure Land, asking whether grain changes practice sequencing.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:27:- Tannisho sections 1, 6, and 8, translation by Taitetsu Unno, https://nembutsu.cc/buddhism/the-tannisho/tannisho-sections-i-to-x/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:29:Structural observation: SN 45.8 parses the path through practitioner-cultivated functions: right view, resolve, speech, action, livelihood, effort, mindfulness, and concentration. The grammar permits the practitioner to perform decisive training functions, though under Buddhist doctrinal constraints. Tannisho shifts decisive efficacy away from self-power and toward entrusting, Other Power, and the Primal Vow, while also warning against claiming disciples or treating nembutsu as self-owned practice or merit. This supports the candidate's entry-claimant link. It also shows the main risk: the same Shinran material supplies entry grammar, claimant prohibition, danger, and verification language at once, so a prediction test can easily become circular.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:31:Secondary literature gap: The audit searched conversion studies, doctrine-as-grammar theory, religious coping agency styles, sociology of plausibility structures, liminality, situated learning, upaya, Shinran Other Power, Orange grace canons, Dogen practice-realization, religious socialization, and prior Lumenary capacity-ledger audits. It did not fully close-read Augustine against Pelagius, Longchenpa or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals, Sufi bayah and fana texts, Sri Vaishnava prapatti sources, or original-language terms for faith, entrusting, effort, capacity, grace, and agency. That gap blocks a candidate-discovery claim.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:41:- Shinran Tannisho Other Power self power nembutsu not practice good act
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:43:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization are one translation
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:58:- Shinran, Chapter on Practice, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/the-major-expositions/chapter-on-practice/: overlap: Very close for load relocation and forbidden claimant. Shinran's Other Power grammar denies self-power as the decisive basis of liberation and relocates decisive function to the Vow and Name.; difference: Shinran gives a specific Pure Land case, while the candidate proposes a cross-tradition entry and claimant grammar with prediction tests.; novelty impact: High reduction and high anomaly pressure. The candidate may mostly generalize Shinran and grace patterns into coding language.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:59:- Soto Zen teaching on practice and realization, https://www.sotozen.com/eng/library/stories/vol01.html: overlap: Close for practice-realization, where practice is not merely a beginner's method leading later to realization but is already implicated in realization.; difference: The candidate's first-break and claimant categories may not map cleanly onto Dogen-style practice-realization because beginning and fulfillment are deliberately collapsed.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction and strong anomaly pressure. Dogen-style cases may force values such as no-transfer, practice-realization, or analyst-frame-refused.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:65:Unlike Rambo's conversion-process model, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar model, Pargament's religious agency styles, Berger's plausibility structures, upaya pedagogy, liminality theory, Shinran's Other Power grammar, Orange grace theology, religious socialization theory, and Lumenary's Entry-State Ledger, this idea claims that entry mechanism and forbidden claimant form one testable agency grammar, and that a split-source independence audit can determine whether that grammar predicts safeguards and verification practices without circularly reusing the same text as both cause and evidence.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:69:Candidate: Inherited practice and Dogen-style practice-realization cases, especially cradle religious formation and Soto Zen's refusal to separate practice from realization.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:71:Why it strains the model: Inherited formation may have no discrete first-break moment, and practice-realization may refuse the sequence of entry, support transfer, claimant prohibition, safeguard, and later verification. In these cases, the model's entry grammar may be an analyst artifact rather than a native structure.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:73:Confidence effect: Lowers confidence from candidate-discovery range to extended or renamed range until the rubric includes no-threshold, gradual-socialization, practice-realization, and analyst-frame-refused values, then survives blind coding.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:77:- If: Entry doctrine and claimant prohibition are separable variables in at least some traditions. Then: Blind coders using only entry texts can distinguish entry mechanism from forbidden claimant, and those separate codes predict different warning and verification patterns in later manuals with above-chance agreement. Weakens if: Coders cannot separate entry mechanism from claimant rule, or later safeguards can be predicted equally well from generic tradition labels, conversion-stage theory, religious socialization, or Pargament agency styles. Test surface: Split-source manual coding across Shinran Pure Land, Theravada path-factor texts, Orange or Augustinian grace texts, Dogen practice-realization, and Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:78:- If: Strong anti-self-claimant traditions should generate distinctive safeguards against moral license, despair, counterfeit passivity, or self-power contamination. Then: Texts and teachers in Other Power, grace, and surrender-centered traditions repeatedly warn against predictable misuse of non-self-efficacy language, and these warnings differ from effort-centered path warnings. Weakens if: Warnings are not distinctive, are mostly generic moral warnings, or are better predicted by institutional history, teacher style, sectarian polemic, or social setting than by claimant grammar. Test surface: Primary manuals, sermons, letters, and practitioner interviews in Jodo Shinshu, Christian grace traditions, bhakti or prapatti, and Sufi tawakkul.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:79:- If: Hybrid or cross-training friction should often occur at claimant boundaries, not only at doctrine or technique boundaries. Then: Practitioners moving between effort-centered, grace-centered, teacher-recognition-centered, and practice-realization paths report confusion about who or what is allowed to own progress, failure, verification, or decisive transformation. Weakens if: Reported friction clusters around vocabulary, social identity, ritual preference, or teacher relationship without identifiable claimant-boundary conflicts. Test surface: Structured interviews with dual-trained practitioners and teachers, coded independently from doctrinal affiliation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:85:- Jodo Shinshu ministers and Shinran scholars
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:88:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen's practice-realization
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:89:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with pointing-out instruction
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:121:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.72 to about 0.58. The idea is not a discovery-level concept. Its entry ecology is strongly anticipated by Rambo, Berger, liminality, situated learning, and religious socialization. Its grammar language is anticipated by Lindbeck. Its agency distribution is anticipated by Pargament and grace or Other Power sources. Its support-locus and safeguard rubric is very close to prior Lumenary Entry-State Ledger, Capacity Ledger, Forbidden Claimant, and Credit Distribution records. The remaining contribution is an extension: an independence audit that tries to prevent construct leakage between entry doctrine, claimant rule, anthropology, safeguard, and verification.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:128:- Add values for no-threshold, inherited socialization, gradual recommitment, crisis threshold, vow-held entry, grace-held entry, teacher-recognition entry, practice-realization, no-transfer, collapsed-transfer, and analyst-frame-refused.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:130:- Use Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, and successful cross-training as anomaly tests, not as supporting examples.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen practice-realization and inherited religious participation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:5:    "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence unless the rubric includes no-threshold, no-break, inherited-practice, practice-realization, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable values, and still makes held-out predictions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Dogen-style practice-realization collapses the ordinary sequence of beginning, method, and fruit. Inherited participation may have no salient first-break event. Both cases strain a model that assumes transformation begins through a narratable threshold and later authorizes a remainder."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:10:    "Traditions authorize or refuse some remainder after critique, such as self, no-self continuity, grace, vow, teacher recognition, practice-realization, ritual, community, or silence.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:36:      "expected_observation": "Teacher-encounter traditions that authorize hidden Self, no-self release, direct recognition, or grace should verify and repair different failures even when the visible entry event looks similar.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:38:      "test_surface": "Paired comparison of Advaita self-inquiry, Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out, Zen encounter, and Christian spiritual direction.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:42:      "expected_observation": "Two traditions that both authorize non-acquired reality should differ if one begins through vow or grace, another through direct recognition, and another through continuous practice-realization.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:44:      "test_surface": "Within-family and cross-family comparisons: Pure Land, Christian grace, Soto Zen, Dzogchen, and Advaita.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:48:      "expected_observation": "High-circularity paths should rely more on vow, grace, teacher authorization, ritual threshold, paradox pedagogy, community holding, or no-threshold practice-realization.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:68:    "\"Tannisho\" Other Power self-power Primal Vow chapter 11",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:69:    "\"Dogen\" Bendowa practice realization shusho itto",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:88:      "difference": "Rites-of-passage theory does not focus on what remains authorized after self-critique, no-self, grace, vow, or practice-realization.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:106:      "difference": "Tannisho is one tradition-internal case, not a cross-tradition predictive rubric.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:107:      "novelty_impact": "Very high reduction for Pure Land examples and strong pressure against recoding Other Power as practitioner capacity.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:109:      "source": "Shinran and Tannisho Other Power sources, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:112:      "difference": "The candidate can include this as no-threshold or practice-realization, but Dogen is not easily treated as entry plus later residue.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:115:      "source": "Dogen practice-realization and shusho itto, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:141:    "Add mandatory values for no-threshold, no-break, inherited practice, gradual socialization, vow-held entry, grace-held entry, teacher-recognition, practice-realization, radical Other Power, ritual-first entry, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:147:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.53. The synthesis is useful and testable, but most components have strong near-neighbors: conversion theory for entry process, rites-of-passage theory for thresholds, Lindbeck for grammar, Pargament for agency distribution, Shinran and Orange for vow or grace-held beginnings, Dogen for practice-realization collapse, VCE for factor-separated contemplative outcomes, and prior Lumenary audits for residue, first-break, entry-state, threshold grammar, claimability, support, and operational remainder ecology. The remaining contribution is a split-source interaction test with additive predictive burden.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:150:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say the framework is obvious as self-power versus Other Power, grace versus works, upaya, conversion stages, or doctrine-as-grammar, and it would not alter sequencing, warning, verification, or repair. They cannot identify cases where the interaction predicts more than teacher experience, tradition identity, social context, or clinical risk.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:164:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:174:      "Tannisho, sections 1, 6, 10, and 11, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:176:      "Dogen Bendowa and shusho itto, Soto Zen source, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:180:    "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit checked accessible primary translations, local prior Lumenary audits, and open sources on conversion, rites of passage, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, situated learning, Pure Land Other Power, Christian grace, and practice-realization. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's full book, Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Latin, or Chinese originals, Shinran scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Sufi bayah and fana sources, Dzogchen pointing-out manuals, or practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:181:    "structural_observation": "The primary texts support an interaction field but also reduce originality. Tannisho makes entry depend on entrusting to Amida's vow, relocates decisive efficacy to Other Power, and warns against self-power, teacher ownership, and self-will. SN 22.59 negates ownership of the five aggregates and moves through disenchantment, release, and knowledge of release, without authorizing a hidden self as remainder. Dogen strains the sequence because practice and realization are one, so beginning and fruit cannot be cleanly separated. The Gita complicates the model by mixing action, multiple causes, divine inner rulership, and final surrender, so one text may contain several entry-residue logics by chapter and voice."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.json:190:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Rambo, Van Gennep, Turner, Lindbeck, Pargament, Lave and Wenger, VCE, Shinran, Dogen, Orange, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says the key test is additive prediction: independently coded residue authorization and entry grammar should interact to predict held-out safeguards, warnings, effort theories, verification rules, and repairs better than entry-only, residue-only, agency-style, social-ecology, tradition-identity, or source-layer baselines."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dzogchen or Mahamudra luminous selfless awareness, plus Pseudo-Dionysius's claim that the divine Cause is beyond both affirmation and negation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:42:      "test_surface": "Close-reading corpus of Theravada, Advaita, Christian apophatic, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra manuals.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:89:    "Close-read Dzogchen and Mahamudra instructions on rigpa or luminous awareness against Bahiya and Brihadaranyaka before publishing the custody model.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:108:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
observations/codex/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return.md:11:A practice is not complete when it gives a person an experience. It is complete only when it teaches the person how to return. The live question has two parts: does the method let the result stand, or does it undermine every claim to have a result; and after the result, is the method kept, set down, or carried as conduct? The Mandukya leans toward a result that can be known. The Heart Sutra undermines attainment while still retaining reliance. MN 22 validates right use and then warns against carrying the raft. Rinzai koan work can exhaust ordinary thinking while remaining a formal curriculum. Dogen strains the whole sequence by making practice and realization one. The practical danger is not only false insight. It is turning a method into proof of worth, or abandoning it before it has trained ordinary conduct.
observations/codex/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return.md:24:- Dogen Uji source card and prior Bendowa practice-realization anomaly in local observations. Used as pressure against any model that assumes a clean before and after.
observations/codex/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return.md:33:The model may still be a modern sorting tool placed over traditions that would reject the frame. Dogen's practice-realization identity is the hardest anomaly: if practice and realization are one, then asking what happens after completion may already distort the source. Tannisho-style Other Power and inherited communal religion would also strain the model because the practitioner may not own the decisive method at all. A second weakness is prior art: Asad, Lindbeck, Weber, Sharf, Katz, Hori, and VCE-style research already show that practice, authority, worldview, institution, and interpretation shape religious experience. The model should be weakened if split-source coding cannot predict held-out warnings or re-entry rules better than institution type, teacher style, tradition label, or ordinary social authority.
observations/codex/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return.md:89:The three-box completion model was weakened by MN 22, Heart Sutra reliance, Rinzai curriculum, Dogen practice-realization, authority-boundary prior art, and modern perfectionism and burnout pressure. The surviving teaching is narrower: test the return, not the peak.
observations/codex/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return.md:164:- Next action: Create a code sheet and test Mandukya Advaita, Heart Sutra, MN 22, Rinzai koan training, Dogen, Tannisho, Dionysius, and one Sufi source with held-out warning passages.
observations/codex/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return.md:194:- Next action: Search and close-read authority, doctrine-as-grammar, contemplative adverse-effects, upaya, raft, ladder, thorn-removes-thorn, and practice-realization scholarship.
observations/codex/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return.md:201:- Close-read Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, Tannisho, Cloud of Unknowing, Dionysius, one Dzogchen pointing-out manual, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before raising confidence.
