reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "In inherited formation, there may be no discrete threshold act, no single first break, and no separate residue policy available to the beginner. In Dogen-style practice-realization, beginning and realization are not cleanly separated, so the entry grammar may be the same as the fruition grammar. These cases force the model to include no-threshold, no-break, continuous-authorization, practice-realization, and analyst-frame-refused values."
