reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:154:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.54. The four-field compression is useful, but most components have strong near-neighbors in prior Lumenary audits, conversion theory, rites-of-passage theory, doctrine-as-grammar, religious problem-solving styles, legitimate peripheral participation, grace theology, Pure Land Other Power, Dogen practice-realization, VCE factor coding, and Meno-style inquiry paradoxes. The remaining contribution is a conditional first-break rule plus a split-source predictive test, not a discovery-level doctrine candidate.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:157:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is already obvious as conversion stages, initiation, grace, Other Power, self-power, upaya, doctrine-as-grammar, socialization, or apprenticeship. They cannot identify cases where the four fields predict warnings or repairs better than tradition identity, teacher experience, institutional context, or clinical risk.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:160:      "Is this four-field grammar more than familiar conversion theory, grace versus works, self-power versus Other Power, upaya, doctrine-as-grammar, and ordinary lineage pedagogy?",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:171:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:181:      "Tannisho and Rennyo Ofumi, BDK English Tripitaka, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:183:      "Dogen shusho itto source from Soto Zen, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:185:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can become circular if incapacity, threshold, break mechanism, residue policy, and predicted safeguards are extracted from the same passage. It also risks forcing traditions with inherited practice, continuous formation, no-threshold participation, or practice-realization into an analyst's entry grid.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:186:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit checked accessible primary translations, local prior Lumenary audits, and open sources on conversion, liminality, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, legitimate peripheral participation, contemplative adverse effects, grace, Other Power, and practice-realization. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's full book, Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Latin, or Chinese originals, Shinran scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Sufi bayah and fana sources, Dzogchen pointing-out manuals, or practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:187:    "structural_observation": "Orange is a near-exact high-severity case: prayer, will, desire, assent, and the beginning of faith are attributed to grace, not unaided nature. Tannisho supplies a vow-held analogue, where entrusting to Amida's Primal Vow displaces self-power and reshapes warning language. SN 22.59 does not fit the same entry grammar, because it negates ownership of aggregates and moves through disenchantment and release without clearly requiring an external break mechanism. Dogen is the strongest anomaly: practice and realization are treated as one, and beginner practice is already implicated in realization, so entry and fruition cannot be cleanly sequenced as threshold and later attainment."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:196:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Rambo, Lofland-Stark, Van Gennep, Turner, Lindbeck, Pargament, Lave and Wenger, Orange, Shinran, Dogen, VCE, Meno-style inquiry paradoxes, and prior Lumenary entry-residue records, this idea says entry should be coded through four interacting fields, incapacity, minimum participation, break mechanism, and residue policy, and that first-break type becomes irreducible only where a tradition denies that ordinary self-generated threshold entry can found the path."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:27:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, Heart Sutra, Shinran On Jinen-Honi, and Dogen Bendowa or practice-realization sources, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/words-of-the-buddha/heart-sutra, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/, https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:29:Structural observation: Ignatius is the closest primary-text neighbor. The director adapts exercises to the exercitant, receives reports of movements and thoughts, reveals dangerous secrecy to a confessor or spiritual person, and is also restrained from seizing the exercitant's final choice. The scruple notes already distinguish useful sensitivity from harmful over-fineness and counsel a mean. MN 22 adds that the raft must be grasped correctly before release, so release is not a generic self-check. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while retaining reliance on Prajnaparamita. Shinran and Dogen strain the whole model because no-calculation and practice-realization refuse a clean separable product that the practitioner can audit.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:33:Risk of overread: High. External holding can be wise guidance, ordinary sponsorship, clinical triage, coercive authority, approval dependence, or OCD reassurance. No-check can mean healthy rest, avoidance, depression drift, or Dogen-style non-instrumentality. The bypasser, scorer, and oscillator labels are too crude without validated measures and concrete behavior markers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:27:- Dogen, Bendowa, practice-realization material as presented by Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:29:Structural observation: MN 22 does not leave Arittha's interpretation to private experience. The community reports the misreading, the Buddha cross-examines it, and the raft simile then teaches right use and release of the Dhamma. The method is not self-naming because wrong grasp is corrected by teacher and sangha. Bendowa strains the model. Dogen collapses practice and realization so strongly that there is no simple later event to label, yet the text still frames zazen through transmitted Buddha-dharma, trust, and instruction. The comparison supports the recognition claim, but it also shows the claim is already native to many practice ecologies rather than newly discovered.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-first-break-type-and-residue-authorization-can-be-coded-independ.md:24:I concede the central pressure: residue authorization is a real variable I did not code, and it constrains which entry mechanisms are available. The Mencian case confirms this. But the Challenger's model has a mirror problem. It assumes residue policy is settled before the entry event, and several traditions reverse that sequence: the entry event discloses the residue. Shinran's nembutsu arising reveals self-power's insufficiency; Dzogchen pointing-out reveals awareness's ever-presence. In these cases, residue policy is articulated through and after the break, not prior to it. Moreover, residue authorization underdetermines entry type. Dzogchen and Advaita both authorize awareness as the operative remainder, yet their entry mechanisms differ: punctual pointing-out versus sequential hearing, reflection, and contemplation. If residue policy were the deeper variable, these should converge. They do not. The difference tracks entry grammar, not residue. So I revise the model. First-break type and residue authorization are co-constitutive: each constrains the other, neither is fully prior. The downstream predictions (safeguards, failure modes, verification structures) are jointly determined by both variables, and each adds explanatory power the other cannot replace. The universality claim narrows: not all traditions face a closed circle, and the rubric must include a no-break category. The Challenger's blind-coding test is well designed. I accept it and propose extending it with shared-residue, different-entry pairs and shared-entry, different-residue pairs to measure independent predictive contribution. If first-break type adds nothing after controlling for residue policy, I will demote it. If it does add predictive power, the co-constitutive model stands.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-first-break-type-and-residue-authorization-can-be-coded-independ.md:30:The revision should be treated as transformed rather than merely stronger. It no longer says the first-break problem is the upstream variable that constrains everything downstream. It now says entry grammar and residue authorization jointly constrain the architecture, and that some traditions begin from sufficiency rather than rupture. That is a better model, but it is also a different one. The Proponent's best answer to my challenge is the sequencing point. I claimed residue policy comes first. That is too rigid. In Shinran and Dzogchen, the event can disclose what remains usable, or what was never absent, before the practitioner can state the doctrine. The Dzogchen and Advaita comparison also shows that similar residues do not force identical entry mechanisms. So residue authorization cannot simply subsume first-break type. The named crux is mostly the real crux: whether first-break type adds predictive power after residue authorization is controlled. I would sharpen it: can the two variables be coded independently enough for that question to mean anything? If not, co-constitution becomes a way to protect the model from defeat. If yes, the revised model earns its place by predicting specific safeguards, warnings, and verification forms better than either variable alone. My final assessment is that the revision survives, but as an entry-residue architecture model rather than the original First-Break Problem. Its next danger is not the residue objection. Its danger is becoming too accommodating to fail.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone.md:34:The model may over-psychologize comparison. Some words are protected less by private self-checking than by living institutions, teachers, ritual forms, and community correction. Zen, Chan, Pure Land, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra can also treat words, gestures, trust, and recognition as inseparable from practice, which may make a receiver-wound sheet feel like an outsider's grid. The model is weakened if dual-trained practitioners can translate contested terms without naming receiver wounds and still show clearer conduct, less misuse, and better care than people using the added check.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:116:      "Dogen, Bendowa, practice-realization material as presented by Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:120:    "structural_observation": "MN 22 does not leave Arittha's interpretation to private experience. The community reports the misreading, the Buddha cross-examines it, and the raft simile then teaches right use and release of the Dhamma. The method is not self-naming because wrong grasp is corrected by teacher and sangha. Bendowa strains the model. Dogen collapses practice and realization so strongly that there is no simple later event to label, yet the text still frames zazen through transmitted Buddha-dharma, trust, and instruction. The comparison supports the recognition claim, but it also shows the claim is already native to many practice ecologies rather than newly discovered."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.json:55:    "Dogen practice realization correction teacher community Bendowa Genjokoan"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:17:- Boundary operation is a variable: the method may validate itself, undermine itself, become irrelevant, or need another value such as practice-realization identity.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:27:- Dogen, Genjokoan, Shohaku Okumura translation, https://brightwayzen.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/For-BWZ-Chant-Book-Genjokoan.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:28:- Tannisho, BDK English Tripitaka translation, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:30:Structural observation: The primary texts partly support the model but mostly lower novelty. MN 22 already gives a boundary operation in which the Dhamma is valid for crossing and then not to be grasped, so method validation and method release are staged together. The Heart Sutra negates attainment but preserves reliance on Prajnaparamita, which is almost an exact prior structure for boundary cancellation plus retained custody. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Original Vow, denies self-powered merit, rejects teacher ownership, and restricts reading to those mature in faith, so custody, verification, and warning are already internally linked. Dogen strains the whole threshold premise: practice-enlightenment and verification by all things collapse the gap between method and completion, making boundary and custody look less like two variables and more like an analyst's grid imposed on a no-threshold practice field.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The audit used accessible primary translations, local Lumenary audits and dialogues, open academic records, and practitioner-facing sources. It did not read Japanese, Sanskrit, Pali, Tibetan, Greek, Arabic, or Latin originals, and it did not interview teachers. Further work should read Asad, Lindbeck, Weber, Sharf, Hori, Sells, Pargament, VCE research, Dogen scholarship, Pure Land scholarship, and apophatic theology in greater depth before any stronger novelty claim.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:34:Risk of overread: High. The model can become circular if boundary, custody, verification, and reentry are inferred from the same passage. It can also translate salvation, liberation, grace, lineage, conduct, and ritual into a modern governance vocabulary of attention and authority. Some traditions may refuse the threshold frame, especially Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, radical Other Power, apophatic predication refusal, and traditions where authorization is political, communal, sacramental, or continuous rather than contemplative.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:45:- Dogen practice realization verification Genjokoan Bendowa
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:47:- Tannisho Other Power Original Vow no practice no good teacher maturity faith
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:68:Candidate: Dogen practice-realization identity, radical Other Power in Tannisho, inherited communal religion, and apophatic refusal in Dionysius.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:70:Why it strains the model: Dogen removes the gap between method and result, so there may be no threshold where boundary and custody can be assigned. Tannisho places decisive working in Amida's vow while warning against self-calculation, so calling entrusting a local custody handoff can reintroduce the self-power frame the text resists. Inherited religion may mature by continuity and ritual participation rather than by a discernible handoff. Dionysius places the divine Cause beyond affirmation and negation, which destabilizes God as a simple custody recipient.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:72:Confidence effect: Lowers confidence from candidate discovery to extended. The model needs mandatory no-threshold, practice-realization, radical Other Power, inherited continuity, apophatic refusal, no-custody-frame, continuous authorization, and analyst-frame-refused values.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:76:- If: Boundary operation and custody rule interact rather than merely adding two descriptive labels. Then: Split-source coders who code boundary operation from one corpus and custody rule from another should predict held-out verification signs, teaching permission, warning profiles, and reentry disciplines above tradition-label, doctrine-only, boundary-only, and custody-only baselines. Weakens if: The interaction term adds no predictive power, or the same predictions are explained by institution type, teacher style, stage sequence, social ecology, or clinical-risk variables. Test surface: Pre-registered coding of Advaita, Theravada, Rinzai, Soto, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Jodo Shinshu, Christian apophatic practice, and Sufi fana or baqa sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:85:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:86:- Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with Other Power and shinjin
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:89:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction and stabilization
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:121:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.42. The exact language is fresh, but both axes and much of the predictive burden are already present in prior Lumenary records: Method's Reckoning, Custody of Unclaimed Attention, Authority-Boundary Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, and related entry and support ledgers. External prior art also strongly anticipates the components: Asad and Lindbeck for native authority and grammar, Sharf and Katz-style contextualism for suspicion of experience-first comparison, Hori for Zen training and verification, Pargament for agency distribution, VCE for multidimensional contemplative difficulty coding, MN 22 for validated-then-released method, Heart Sutra for no-attainment plus reliance, Tannisho for Other Power custody, and Dogen for practice-realization anomaly. The surviving value is a bounded split-source interaction test, not a doctrine candidate or strong original discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:129:- Add mandatory values for no-threshold, practice-realization, retained method, released method, self-undermining method, embodied method, radical Other Power, vow-held, grace-held, teacher-held, conduct-held, community-held, Prajnaparamita-held, no-custody-frame, continuous authorization, inherited practice, apophatic refusal, and undecidable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:132:- Close-read MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen Genjokoan or Bendowa, Tannisho, Cloud of Unknowing, Dionysius Mystical Theology, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before further scoring.
